metadata.name: 0x
metadata.bio:
0x is developers’ one-stop shop to build financial products on crypto rails. 0x empowers hundreds of developers with essential web3 tools to enable faster trading, better prices and superior UX. Our suite of APIs has processed over 60M+ million transactions and $154B+ in volume from more than 9+ million users trading on apps like Coinbase Wallet, Robinhood Wallet, Phantom, Metamask, Zerion, Zapper, and more.

Founded in 2017 by Will Warren and Amir Bandeali, the 0x team is also the creator of the decentralized exchange Matcha. The team has made significant technical contributions, including the NFT token standard (ERC721), the creation of Wrapped ETH, and has raised $109M up to Series B from leading investors as Pantera Capital, Greylock and Coinbase.

name: All the Ink Ran Out While I Was Living

metadata.name: All the Ink Ran Out While I Was Living
metadata.bio:
I continued writing poems, they were among the things I never gave up. Another was of course drawing portraits with ink pens as well as pencils. Portraits changed over time, becoming more complex but with simpler lines. It was all so simple to me, but I know other eyes looking at them wouldn't know what was simple and what wasn't. I kept discovering new words, kept writing until my fingers were covered in blue and black ink. I never washed my hands, I wanted to leave a trace of the past. I wanted my hands to leave simple stains when I applied them to my face. Of course, those who saw me would first laugh and then ignore me, just as I wanted. 

November, 2023 
by Demon Ego

metadata.name: Ancurated: Preserving Culture On-Chain
metadata.bio:
Ancurated is an artist-led production company dedicated to preserving and elevating culture through curated and experiential projects. By integrating the power of technology, physical art, and editorial narratives, we create opportunities that celebrate and protect the rich cultural stories of Africa and its Diaspora, ensuring they are represented and preserved on-chain. As Head of Media, I assisted in developing the marketing and structure for our on-chain summer experience. 

During OnChain Summer, Ancurated spearheaded multiple groundbreaking projects on the Superchain, highlighting diverse talents from Africa and the African Diaspora. We believe in the critical importance of safeguarding and amplifying these interconnected stories, breaking barriers to showcase the vast and diverse artistic expressions from across the African continent and beyond. Our mission is clear: Africa is not a monolith but a continent of vast influence and creativity that resonates globally.

Key Projects:

Ancollective: We launched Ancollective, an African-based guild fostering a vibrant community for the next generation of African artists on the blockchain. Ancollective is now one of the largest African-based accounts on Zora, with a following of 3.5k. Through this platform, we’ve onboarded 15 artists from various regions of Africa. As part of ancollective, we also developed their own digital zine "The Community Chronicle." Our special "Africa Day" edition achieved 213 mints and attracted 163 collectors, a record that underscores the impact of our efforts to educate and celebrate African history, created through the support of AI technology and IRL stories. (wallet address on zora : 0x8344d047332b3c8f5573fd54a87025c5e9409698)

REMX and Base Collaboration: Partnering with REMX, a platform bridging digital assets with physical art, we curated a drop featuring the artist vintagemozart. His piece "Stable Environment," sold out to 600 collectors, marking a significant milestone in his journey toward physical art. (wallet address: 0x1b44c859a41a57ba05e380b0eb803481ea342c74)

Fxhash "OnChain Summer" Partnership: In collaboration with Fxhash, we curated Ngozi Nao’s generative on-chain collection "Ultimate Time Crystal" via Base. This collection, reflecting her passion for time, space, and astrology, was a resounding success, with 349 NFTs sold and 135 unique owners. Alongside this, we produced a digital zine, "16x9," offering an editorial deep dive into her creative process, resulting in 118 mints and 30 unique holders. (contract address: 0xF0dEeef444E6f5f87f19ba5e90DEBF4F46390A87)

Superchief Gallery Collaboration - "Remote Control": Ancurated was part of the curation team in partnership with Superchief Gallery, showcasing African and Diaspora artists in a unique vote-driven event. We picked seven artists from West Africa, the Caribbean, and Southern Africa regions, with Swiss-Ugandan artist Samora 'Oibel1' Bazarrabusa winning the top spot and being showcased in Times Square for the first time in his career. Overall, our curated selection garnered 154 votes, uniting the community in a powerful celebration of African and Diaspora art. (wallet address: 0x1b44c859a41a57ba05e380b0eb803481ea342c74)

Through these projects, Ancurated has made significant strides in promoting and protecting African and Diaspora cultures, leveraging the blockchain to ensure these stories and talents are preserved and celebrated globally.

From towering landscapes that seem to reach into the heavens to intimate moments imbued with an otherworldly glow, each photograph in the series offers a glimpse into a dimension where the rules of reality are rewritten. Embracing the interplay between light and shadow, "Anomalies" invites audiences to question the boundaries of existence and contemplate the infinite possibilities that lie beyond our comprehension.

Embark on a journey of discovery and wonder as you immerse yourself in the captivating imagery of "Anomalies." Let go of preconceived notions and allow yourself to be transported to a realm where the extraordinary becomes the norm, and the line between reality and fantasy blurs into oblivion.

name: Art - To say the word fool correctly

metadata.name: Art - To say the word fool correctly
metadata.bio:
Ah, the melodious intonation of the word "fool," a term that has tickled the tongues of jesters and philosophers alike! To articulate it correctly is an art form, a delicate balance between playful derision and affectionate teasing.

First, let us prepare the stage for our vocal cords, for they are the unsung heroes in this comedic concerto. Begin with a furrowed brow and a knowing smirk, as if you're about to unveil the universe's greatest secret, or perhaps just remembered a particularly funny joke at an inopportune moment.

Now, for the grand performance: The 'f' should escape your lips like a mischievous whisper, the soft harbinger of hilarity to come. It's the gentle rustle of a jester's bells, the sly wind before the storm of snickers.
As we glide into the 'oo,' let it roll out like a red carpet of ridicule, stretching long and full of pomp. This is the heart of the word, the soulful song of the scamp. It should resonate with the roundness of a court jester's belly, full from feasting on the folly of others.

Finally, we arrive at the 'l,' the crisp finale, the flick of the trickster's wand. It should not be a harsh 'l,' but rather a soft landing, a subtle nod to the buffoonery that has just danced upon our lips.

And there you have it, a fool said with such grace and gusto that it almost seems a compliment. Remember, to say "fool" with the right lilt is to walk the tightrope between jest and jab, a verbal wink that lets the listener in on the joke. It's a word that, when wielded with humor and irony, can turn the most stoic of faces into a canvas of chuckles.

Now go forth and practice this artful articulation, for the world is in dire need of fools, pronounced ever so foolishly, to keep the solemn specter of seriousness at bay.

metadata.name: AstraDeFi
metadata.bio:
AstraDeFi provides a powerful staking feature, allowing users to lock their tokens and earn staking rewards without sacrificing liquidity. This ensures that users can continue to earn while still having the flexibility to manage their assets as needed. The platform’s staking mechanism is built to maximize returns while maintaining the security and integrity of user assets.

In addition to staking, AstraDeFi enables users to provide liquidity to Automated Market Maker (AMM) pools. By contributing to these pools, users not only earn a share of transaction fees but also enhance the overall liquidity of the platform, facilitating smoother and more efficient trading for everyone involved. The AMM pools within AstraDeFi are optimized for low slippage and high liquidity, ensuring that trades are executed quickly and fairly.

AstraDeFi also features a swap functionality, allowing users to effortlessly exchange tokens within the platform. With an intuitive interface and minimal transaction costs, AstraDeFi ensures that users can execute trades seamlessly, making it easier than ever to participate in the DeFi ecosystem.

Moreover, AstraDeFi includes advanced analytics tools that provide users with deep insights into their investments and the broader market. These tools help users make informed decisions by offering real-time data on liquidity, trading volumes, and price movements, all within a single platform.

AstraDeFi stands out not only for its features but also for its integration with cutting-edge technologies from ETHGlobal partners like Mode, Base, Blockscout Optimism, and Goldsky. These partnerships bring additional layers of innovation, security, and scalability to the platform, ensuring that AstraDeFi remains at the forefront of the DeFi revolution.

In summary, AstraDeFi is a versatile and user-friendly DeFi platform that brings together staking, liquidity provision, AMM pools, and token swapping, all underpinned by powerful analytics. Whether you’re an experienced DeFi user or new to the space, AstraDeFi offers the tools and features needed to navigate and thrive in the decentralized financial world.

metadata.name: Avantis
metadata.bio:
Avantis is the Superchain’s first DEX focused on cross-asset leverage (real-world assets and crypto), built on and backed by Base. Avantis allows users to trade and hedge all kinds of assets with leverage, while retaining full custody of their funds. The capital for this comes from onchain LPs who passively market-make all trading activity. 

Since our launch on Base in February this year, we’ve done over $1.2B in trading volumes with $15MM in our capped vaults, and over 17K traders served. We've established ourselves as one of the leading destinations for Superchain perp traders and LPs. We have three simple goals:

1. RWA Adoption: Get more real world asset traders onchain and provide trader exposure to both macro and crypto catalysts. Avantis is the only Superchain DEX where you’d find both BTC and JPY-USD trending on the same day. Even outside the Superchain, Avantis is the largest DEX in DeFi for RWA trading, as measured by open interest.
2. Superchain as a Derivatives Hub: Make the Superchain the premier destination for onchain perpetuals trading and market-making.
3. Democratize Market-Making: Provide competitive and safe yields for LPs while giving them custom risk management tools. Passive LPs should receive the opportunity to market-make complex derivatives the same way institutions do, which is the true and original promise of DeFi.

metadata.name: Avantis
metadata.bio:
GM - We're building Avantis, a fully onchain, generalized leverage trading exchange for synthetic crypto and real assets, built on and backed by Base. Avantis allows traders to long / short all kinds of assets with leverage, while retaining full custody of their funds. The capital for this comes from onchain LPs who passively market-make all trading activity. All trades and liquidity provisioning happens in USDC. 

Since our launch on Base in February this year, here's what we've achieved:

1. 8,400 traders
2. 96,000 trades 
3. Organic yield paid to LPs: $550,000 
4. Total Trading Volume: $550M (10%+ coming from real world assets like forex and metals!). 
5. TVL: $7.5M (capped)

Note: all protocol stats can be verified onchain as well as at: avantisfi.com/analytics
Today, we’re looking to apply to RPGF to revolutionize the derivatives market. While there are several off-chain or hybrid exchanges available, we firmly believe in constructing a completely on-chain future through a permissionless platform for both RWAs and crypto assets, fueled by LPs and traders. We’re exclusive to the Superchain, committed to building a sustainable exchange long-term, and are just getting started.

In a matter of 3 short months, we've established ourselves as one of the leading destinations for Superchain (and specifically Base network) perp traders and LPs. We plan to keep going deeper into the Base stack, having already integrated Coinbase Pay to onramp users seamlessly, and are in the process of integrating CB smart wallets. We have three simple goals: 

1) RWA Adoption: Get more real world asset traders onchain (the onchain market currently lacks this diversity of traders. We believe we can onboard them effectively.)
2) Superchain as a Derivatives Hub: Make Base (and the Superchain) the premier destination for onchain perpetuals trading and market-making. 
3) Democratize market-making: Provide competitive and safe yields for USDC LPs on Base, while giving them custom risk management tools. That is, we want to allow passive LPs the opportunity to market-make complex derivatives the same way institutions do, which is the true and original promise of DeFi.

metadata.name: Awakening
metadata.bio:
Eyes trace her steps, staring, biting deep,
Seeing everything but the soul she keeps.
“Eye candy,” they whisper, and she’s torn,
Feeling judged, lost, and worn.

Appearance seems all that they see,
A term dangled, reducing her to mere allure.
One voice starts, and others follow,
Leaving her feeling hollow.

Fully dressed or bare, makeup or messy,
The eyes follow, questioning what she’s got. 
Pretending or hiding, never truly seen.
Trying to conform, yet always breaking norms,
Breathing alone seems to cause storms.
Walking on eggshells of what’s right, what’s wrong,
In a world where she feels she doesn’t belong.

She yearns to be more, yet feels confined,
Words twist and bind, reflecting minds,
Respect in words should always come through,
For beauty is more than what the eye beholds. ✨

metadata.name: Base Türkiye
metadata.bio:
Live and Let Live!

As we enter the final days of Onchain Summer, we at Base Türkiye have created a commemorative NFT as part of Onchain Summer, where you can earn 5,000 points. All proceeds from the NFT will be donated to LÖSEV, one of Turkey's most established non-governmental organizations.

Our endless thanks to Pika, as well as the teams at Base and Coinbase, for working with us on this project!

Founded in 1998, LÖSEV (The Foundation for Children with Leukemia) is one of the largest non-governmental organizations in Türkiye and Europe, with 80,000+ patients and approximately 7,000,000 volunteers. It fights against childhood cancers, particularly leukemia, raises awareness about these diseases, supports treatment processes and provides financial and emotional assistance to sick children and their families.


Hello everyone!

We have donated the entire amount raised during our campaign, which was featured on the Onchain Summer website for approximately 20 hours, to LÖSEV.

To maintain transparency throughout the process, we are sharing every step with you until the donation reaches LÖSEV. You can follow the progress step by step through the links below:

metadata.name: BCard
metadata.bio:
BCard helps individuals funds communities via everyday card spending.  Every time you swipe a payment card, 1-2% of the total price is paid as a fee to a bank - BCard redirects a portion of those fees to users' favourite web3 communities in exchange for the community's social token.

In addition to our core product, we have also created free tools for web3 communities, a shared password manager (BCard Vault) and a DAO Income tax calculator (Taxman)

metadata.name: Bitsave Protocol
metadata.bio:
WHAT IS BITSAVE?
Bitsave is a savings protocol that helps users save and earn in cryptocurrency without losing their savings due to market volatility.

BITSAVE SOLUTION (simplified)
- Bitsave helps web2 users in African Countries escape inflation in their fiat currencies by saving in dollars.
- The dollar is not easily accessible to the average African.
- Bitsave helps users create an automatic recurring savings plan

We've seen newbies lose their savings like school fees, house rent, college funds etc to Crypto, we understand that people hear about crypto and want to rush in immediately.

With Bitsave, newbies and oldies can protect their funds from market volatility, while still earning interest in crypto, a protocol that works based on maths and economic formulas to set rates and interests.

metadata.name: BLOCKS
metadata.bio:
BLOCKS is a fully onchain, infinite art collection on the Zora network. BLOCKS enables any block on the Zora Network to be "claimed" by a minter, in the form an NFT of that block - with only one NFT per block. To date, over 450,000 BLOCKS have been minted.

The NFT media is dynamic and rendered via onchain SVG, with a unique background color based on the owner's address and text of the block number for that block. Users can also switch their NFT to display into "zorb mode", which displays their NFT with a black background and the owner's customized zorb in the top corner of the NFT.

metadata.name: BMX by Morphex
metadata.bio:
BMX by Morphex offers two types of decentralized perpetual exchanges, enabling increased capital efficiency for liquidity providers and a feature-abundant experience for traders. 

BMX’s “Classic” market offers a standard GMX-style experience enabling the acquisition of BMX-Liquidity-Token (BLT), our equivalent of GLP.

BMX’s “Freestyle” market utilizes the cutting-edge intents-based technology of SYMMIO to unleash access to 200+ tradeable assets with up to 60x leverage. 

This unique design directs revenue from both trading markets to BLT and BMX holders. In terms of TVL metrics, we currently host $2.8mm in trading liquidity, $2.7mm in staked tokens, and $3.3mm in combined pool2 liquidity! We've also processed over $295mm in volume across our Classic and Freestyle markets since launch, attracting >21.4k users!

Traders and liquidity providers can earn stackable yield on their deposited collateral/liquidity through BMX’s innovative asset: wBLT. 

wBLT auto-compounds BLT liquidity rewards, removing the need to manually claim yield for the user. Then, it can be utilized as a collateral asset, to borrow stables or other bluechip assets against it while continuing to earn yield. 

wBLT can also be utilized as a pool2 paired asset, enabling stackable yield for the user, from both perpetual markets in addition to pool2 liquidity rewards!

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: Asides from being a spot and margin DEX, we also offer yield products.

metadata.name: Bot or Not
metadata.bio:
Bot or Not is building tools that help people improve the content they consume on Farcaster. Bot or Not originally launched as one of the first Farcaster Cast Actions and quickly rose into the top 10 on the Warpcast cast actions Discover list.

Since the launch in April, the Bot or Not cast action has been used over 250k times, has had over 10k unique users, has categorized nearly 22k FIDs, and still has an average of 200+ DAUs.

As the database of FID classifications was populated some Farcaster builders reached out wanting access to an API. Apps like https://www.interested.fyi/ and an open source FC client are using a beta version of the API to combat bot-like activity.

And in an attempt to make the data more openly accessible Bot or Not has started to attest classifications on Base using the Ethereum Attestation Service: https://base.easscan.org/schema/view/0x4fad2c558294b9b0d587d7047ccdd8ffbf3f14c0c03bc28471e1a72aef678747

The cast action’s original intent was to help Farcaster users quickly decipher if someone had bot-like casting behavior before they engaged with them. Using a combination of cast history and AI, Bot or Not classifies users and provides a summary of their casting habits so that people can decide for themselves if they want to engage or not.

Since launch, Bot or Not has expanded beyond just the cast action. The database of information on FID classifications is now used to power: 
Farcaptcha - a Captcha frame that is used to combat bot-like activity.
Simple Mod - anti-bot channel moderation that channel owners can set up entirely in frame.
Reply stats - a frame that breaks down how many of your recent replies are from bot-like accounts vs non-bot accounts

name: BRIDGE: North meets South - N3XTWAVE x NEWTRO collective drop

metadata.name: BRIDGE: North meets South - N3XTWAVE x NEWTRO collective drop
metadata.bio:
BRIDGE was a collective synchronized drop on Zora that I conceptualized and organized, with a goal of connecting two distant geo-regions: the North, represented by Europe-based N3XTWAVE Collective, and the South, represented by Newtro Arts Collective who I invited to this project, with the selection of Latin American artists. 
As it says in the Project’s Art Statement that I wrote: 
The BRIDGE theme was inspired by bridging technology - the main mechanism of Layer 2 networks, such as Zora, that connects two separate networks enabling assets to be transferable between them. Just as on the blockchain - in this project - BRIDGE event is a way of bridging the two distant hemispheres and their artist communities, who are joining forces in this massive collective art release.
The BRIDGE code-word with its multiple meanings is the cornerstone of our mission to unite distant regions and build a borderless Web3 community that thrives on diversity and innovation.
This project also aims to bridge the disparities in representation within the art scene between the Global South and the West, seeking to transcend inequalities caused by differing political, economic, and cultural contexts. With this project we want to provide equal opportunities for all artists, and create a more balanced and interconnected global art community that celebrates diversity and different origins as its greatest strength.
We see BRIDGE as a symbol of unity, transformation, progress and endurance.
The BRIDGE drop occurring at the transition from the old to the new year, symbolizes bridging the past and future while embracing a creative intersection of tradition and innovation in the art world.
With our synchronized drop, we hope to make a significant impact shaping the Web3 landscape, while celebrating its accessibility and the wide range of opportunities it offers.
──⬥◆⬥── 
Full info & credits of the BRIDGE Project: 
◆ Concept, Art Statement & Organizing: V5MT ◆ Promo - Animated Flyers + N3XTWAVE Mirror Profile: V5MT ◆ Event Flyer: stipinpixel ◆ VR Gallery initiative: Newtro ◆ VR Gallery builders: UgoDigi & Datura - North side, + Eltito - South side + glb bridge: V5MT + later Eltito optimizing & installing it to connect both sides of the gallery ◆ Release Date: January 3rd 2024 ◆ Platform: zora.co ◆ Network: ZORA ◆ Featured Artists: N3XTWAVE: Bleu281, Francoise Gamma, V5MT, Datura, Jerome Allavena , Lucas Lejeune, Nicholas Dietrich, Ugo, k0ch, Mostwrongking, Element Lee + Newtro Represented LatAm Artists (selected collectively by N3XTWAVE members): cap'n, stipinpixel, mariana Ju, Pipi Universel, Ed Marola, m.suksu, Moranicol , Danyrus, Jotta.rs, Aura, Santiago Ruau.
──⬥── 
Notes:
⬥I'm submitting this project from my personal Farcaster account, not N3XTWAVE, which I set up but didn't have time to manage.⬥Because we decided not to use a collaborative contract for this drop, (since it was a new feature and we weren’t sure how to implement it), I'm linking to my Mirror article with all the minted pieces embedded, instead of linking to Zora.⬥I plan to share the potential reward from this submission and distribute it to the artists accordingly.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: My goal with this project was to unite the two powerful art communities of the global North and South, represented by the N3XTWAVE and Newtro collectives, and to join forces in a synchronized drop.  Due to all of us being very busy - realizing this project took about three months - from my concept and drafting it in a doc, until finally releasing it in January. Through all this time we were communicating with Newtro managers, discussing ideas and the strategy. They asked us to build a Protoworld gallery to showcase this drop in virtual space, which we did thanks to Ugo Digi, who built our section, with help from Datura. To reward their efforts I have shared the income from the N3XTWAVE Support Token that I made for this drop, minting it as a split. Additionally I created a 3D model of a .glb bridge that Eltito from Newtro installed to connect both parts of the virtual gallery. Stipinpixel from Newtro side designed a static promo poster for the event. I coordinated all the organization, made animated flyers, wrote an art statement, and released it on the N3XTWAVE Mirror profile that I set up.

name: Checkin: Location-based “Checkin and Earn” social to connect IRL and onchain

metadata.name: Checkin: Location-based “Checkin and Earn” social to connect IRL and onchain
metadata.bio:
Checkin is a location-based social app built on top of the Farcaster social graph. Users can explore, checkin and earn rewards for discovering the world around them.
  
Checkin Demo:
https://youtu.be/mGKibG2xfhA


## Problem

We believe there is a disconnect between onchain identities and our IRL identities.

Onchain data is only a small part of our identity; most of our lives are offchain or IRL data - IRL data has a lot of signal that can be added to onchain data.

Our conviction is that in the future in order to have meaningful engagement with users, we need to bridge IRL/offchain activities to our onchain identities.
  
Vision
  
Checkin is enriching digital identities by bridging IRL activities to onchain identity.  By tying IRL activities to wallets (e.g. earning a “Ramen Lovers” badge checking into 5 ramen places), Checkin enables users to own their combined IRL and onchain identities, and builders can then create new and exciting experiences with this location/IRL-centric data. The highest signal of your interests is voting with your feet.  Being a location-centric social app that taps into onchain social graphs, we encourage people to be more social and touch grass with friends more often.

When bridging IRL activities to onchain identities, users can benefit from better personalization when interacting with onchain projects. Projects benefit from improved engagement and conversions when they have more context on who their users are beyond financial transactions.

  
 
IRL Social Experiences:
- At ETHCC this year a member of the Checkin community organized a Checkin Challenge tour where they selected a list of local places to ‘checkin’ with other ETHCC attendees.  Over a dozen ETHCC attendees decided to make new friends and explore new surroundings using Checkin
- We partnered with POAP to create “POAP Rally Tokyo” where users can checkin to 9 shrines across Tokyo to earn cool POAPs and a chance to win one of 3 cool darumas designed by a local Japanese artist.  Extending on this we organized 2 walking tours of Tokyo where 20+ people signed up to touch grass and our spirits.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: composable location-based social app with experiences built on top of checkins

metadata.name: Chibi Clash Kingdoms
metadata.bio:
Chibi Clash is a fantasy gaming universe and the first AI-powered game built on Base. Within the Chibi Clash gaming universe, Chibi Kingdoms is the on-chain land meta game that features the largest cohesive map ever created by generative AI. Players take on the roles of warriors or warlords, navigating a dynamic world that evolves based on their actions and decisions.

Key features include:

1) Generative AI -- Land plots in Chibi Kingdoms are visually and narratively connected, forming an expansive and ever-evolving world. New and improved artwork is generated during world events and upgrades, ensuring fresh and dynamic gameplay.

2) Dynamic Play -- Chibi Clash Kingdoms connects to two other games in the universe, each providing unique experiences that blend strategy, adventure, and AI-driven gameplay. This diversity appeals to both casual players and hardcore strategists.

3) Autonomous AI -- Non-player characters roam the lands at will, offering aid or rewards, generating new lore, changing landscapes, and creating new gaming experiences.

Crypto: The Game (CTG) is an interactive, onchain survival game. Contestants buy in with 0.1 ETH, join tribes, participate in daily challenges, and vote each other out over ten-day seasons until one person wins the entire pot. CTG has been compared to Survivor, Hunger Games, and Squid Game. Players have described it as "dramatic and insanity-inducing," and "the most fun crypto experience in years."

CTG, launched as a unique crypto gaming experience, had players strategizing around the clock. They communicated in tribe-specific chats and faced the potential of being voted out by their tribemates each night. They could gain immunity by topping the daily leaderboard in tribal immunity challenges, which ranged from classic arcade games to digital scavenger hunts and crypto puzzles.

CTG S2, built on Base, was designed with only 800 spots available. These spots sold out in 13 minutes, with each 0.1 ETH NFT contributing to a prize pool of nearly $300,000, which one player won. S2 also featured a new minting mechanic built on Base.

Players minted an NFT to secure their spot in The Game. This buy-in contributed toward the grand prize pot. As players were voted out, their NFTs automatically transitioned from "player" to "jury" status, as the final winner is decided by previously eliminated players. This also meant players could sell their NFT at any time, which allowed spectators and former players to buy into the game as it progressed. This mechanic, unique to crypto, created an in-game economy reminiscent of "Deal or No Deal," only possible onchain.

CTG S2 was supported by major sponsors including adidas, Uniswap, Lens, Wormhole, POAP, and Safe, and received media coverage from CoinDesk, Axios, Bankless, Decrypt, and Unchained. Boys Club hosted a daily companion podcast throughout the season. Over 10 days, the season attracted over 100,000 site visits (with more than 50,000 unique visitors), accumulating 4,000+ total hours of gameplay. Players participated from the US, Canada, UK, India, Germany, Hong Kong, Japan, Singapore, France, and the Netherlands. Crypto: The Game S2 was also the first onchain project to be listed on the ballot for a Primteime Emmy Award in the category of Outstanding Emerging Media Program.  

The contract was deployed at 0x4DfC7EA5aC59B63223930C134796fecC4258d093 from a special purpose factory at 0x3AbB25038DA5A6eE9F524CC16C7F7EC68Db7EB3b on the base superchain network.

metadata.name: Daily Process Practice
metadata.bio:
"Daily Process Practice" commenced on January 1st, 2024, serving as a personal framework for engaging in 30 minutes of focused practice in Adobe Photoshop. As part of the accountability process, I committed to minting whatever was on my canvas at the end of these 30 minutes onchain using ZORA. Referred to as the "DPP," this practice was to be completed every weekday, with a limit of 13 available for free. Throughout this year, I've leveraged the mainnet, ZORA, and base chains, gaining firsthand insight into the benefits of L2s for an artist's financial well-being.

I have compiled the initial 69 Daily Process Practices into a physical book titled "Daily Process Practice" by 1HESAGER, which is now available on Metalabel. The book is equipped with an IYK NFC chip for an On-Cyber gallery tour hosted by the artist. Each piece is accompanied by personal background narratives, and the collection aims to foster community engagement and preserve creative practices for future generations.

metadata.name: Dark Forest Ares
metadata.bio:
Dark Forest Ares is an community-maintained sovereign version of Dark Forest. 

Dark Forest is a fully onchain MMORTS game that utilizes zkSNARKs and operates on EVM-compatible chains. The Dark Forest official team has not introduced new rounds since the early 2022. Driven by our belief in the onchain MMO vision and our passion for Dark Forest, our team (DFArchon) decided to maintaining Dark Forest Ares. We aim to explore different game mechanics while maintaining the original style of the game.

From early 2023 to mid-2024, we released 4 different game versions of DFAres, from v0.1.1 to v0.1.4. During those four rounds, we primarily introduced long-range attack artifacts such as Ice Link and Fire Link, area-of-effect artifacts including the Nuclear Bomb and Kardashev, a union system designed to facilitate player group competition, and a bounty system targeting planet killers. Additionally, we modified the ZK circuits to enable controllable generation of cosmic resources without revealing the exact coordinates of the planets.

metadata.name: dHEDGE Base
metadata.bio:
dHEDGE is a decentralized non-custodial tokenized vault protocol built on Ethereum L2’s including Optimism and Base. 

The protocol facilitates  non-custodial management of assets between individuals seeking to allocate funds and vault managers with an onchain track record of performance. These vault managers have special privileges including trading assets on depositors behalf, using whitelisted protocols, collecting management fees, and making updates to the tradable assets of vaults. In addition, users can utilize automatic yield and leveraged vaults.

Through these vaults, structured products can be created using automation, such as mStable and Toros Finance. Some of the successful products include: derivative, yield, and index vaults.

653 vaults are deployed across Optimism and Base by the dHEDGE factory contracts.

metadata.name: Dia
metadata.bio:
In a categorization of people, acts, and things into squares, we realize that each day of our lives can be represented by a unique mixture. A composition that can be dense or light, colorful or not, reflecting the complexity and diversity of our experiences. The distortion and noise, layered over squares in seemingly random positions, add a depth that celebrates the beauty and unpredictability of life. Each square is a window to a moment, a memory, or an emotion, composing a mosaic of order and disorder, clarity and obscurity, highlighting how our lives are shaped by both moments of clarity and periods of confusion and uncertainty

The project consists of generative code written in p5.js and GLSL. The stacking and overlapping squares are part of my personal research on the categorization of moments, feelings, and experiences. Through rectangles, dense or not, that overlap and distort, I can convey an image of what a “day” filled with moments and experiences grouped together would be.

The project includes 22 color palettes and infinite possibilities for composition.

metadata.name: Dreamworld
metadata.bio:
I am a dreamer and a romantic, and I like to convey the feeling of unreality in my photography; the fragile feeling of magic in the frame is important to me. I like it to feel like a dream.

My photography is about life in imaginary worlds. Angels and mermaids exist there, whatever you want can be there. I
am fascinated by the connection between nature and people, and I feel a fragile calm in this connection.

Mermaids captures the ethereal beauty of mysterious underwater worlds, bringing to life the mesmerizing world of mythical sea creatures. Invites viewers on a visual journey, exploring the boundaries between dreams and reality.

And this year in winter, when I was haunted by dark emotions, I found in them inspiration for exploring floral photography. My immersion in the search for otherworldly flowers from the world of dreams. Partly this is my self-portrait, partly it’s my view of the world and my dreams. This is my personal feeling, unrequited love and drama are hidden there, my story is there. And everything is blurred by the unreality of reality.

As a result, I can say that photography is my life, my path and my way to connect with our world! Through it I connect with a sense of harmony.

metadata.name: Elemnts by Ohnahji
metadata.bio: The Elemnts collection is a generative python script for Blender 4.0 that explores the fundamental building blocks of nature through abstract, isometric rectangular prisms. Each work randomly selects colors from its elemental palette, creating a unique interplay of hues and forms that embody the essence of earth, wood, fire, water, or metal. The white background serves as a canvas for these elemental expressions, allowing the vibrant, geometric shapes to emerge in perfect isometric alignment, offering a fresh perspective on the classical elements that shape our world.

metadata.name: Envio
metadata.bio:
Envio is a modular data stack with a core focus on delivering superior performance and seamless developer experience, our solutions empower Superchain developers and apps to thrive. Apps like Velodrome.finance (Dex for OP Superchain), Aerodrome.finance (Base Dex), Brid.gg (Base and OP Superchain bridge), Limitless.exchange (Predication & Betting Markets), Degen Steaks (Farcaster Frame), Sablier.com (Payments across 12+ chains), and a lot more (150+ apps) are built on Envio.

We host and maintain mission-critical accelerated data infra for these apps across most OP stack chains in the Superchain and align with the Superchain's vision and mission. 

Visit the Notion page linked in this application for more info on how we support the Superchain mission, and applications on the Superchain.

metadata.name: ETERNAL GARDEN // ZERO
metadata.bio:
ETERNAL GARDEN // ZERO is a drop that features 5 independent music artists who have entered the Eternal Garden story as main characters (TK, Sara Phillips, Kaien Cruz, Refi Sings, Domino and Kevin George), each with their own expansive storyline, accompanying AI-generated character visuals and music.

The drop includes the ability to purchase a digital (redacted) and/or physical copy of the CODEX, a stunning visual guide to Eternal Garden powered by AI with integrated characters and an AR component: By scanning each page collectors can experience animation, narrations, and the ZERO album. Collectors could also mint the individual artist music videos and/or tracks separately at an accessible price.

Each modal of the drop was distributed and sold onchain, including the purchase of the digital and physical CODEX copies, the music album and music videos as well as digital shoe. In two phases we have generated ~35+ ETH in volume and amassed over 26,000 collectors on Base network. 

// Eternal Garden is a sci-fi fantasy epic about a mystical seed that has the power to spawn infinite worlds //

metadata.name: ethOS - The Ethereum Phone
metadata.bio: We are the Freedom Factory. We have built ethOS, a free and open source OS that embraces Ethereum. ethOS unlocks the full potential of Web3. It features an onboard Ethereum light node and a System-level wallet, allowing for direct interaction between mobile applications and Ethereum, seamless switching between L1 and L2s (including Optimism), and gives users more security and control over their assets by leveraging device biometrics and notifications. We released the first build of ethOS in 7/22, starting with a fork of Android that could be flash installed on Pixel3 devices. We launched ethOS v2.0 at ETH Denver 2023, and in 8/23 we sold out of 50 Pixel 7a devices that come preinstalled with ethOS v3. We develop fast, and have a long list of existing functionality and features of ethOS.

metadata.name: Event Horizon DEX
metadata.bio:
Event Horizon is an innovative decentralized exchange (DEX) platform on its own exchange-optimized L2 Rollup within the Op-stack Superchain. Offering users secure, fast, and convenient cryptocurrency trading. Our mission is to provide financial freedom and accessibility for everyone.

Key Features:

Hybrid Model: Event Horizon is developing a new generation of hybrid DEX that combines the best qualities of centralized and decentralized solutions. Trade directly from decentralized wallet in a single transaction with off-chain order book, on-chain settlement, MPC, and self-custody.

Matcher: Ensures high transaction speed through rapid order matching. This technological component allows using an off-chain order book with on-chain settlements. Creates flexibility in order management that is not possible with blockchain solutions.

L2 Rollup: Developing our own L2 Rollup based on the Op-Stack Superchain, which allows us to leverage all the advantages of the EVM network while reducing transaction costs by 10 to 100 times. Block mining time will be 2-5 seconds, which is significantly faster than that of traditional networks.

Account Abstraction (ERC 4337): Allows enhanced security and improves user experience through two-factor authentication for withdrawals and large transactions. Additionally, Account Abstraction will enable features like account recovery through governance voting.

Team: Our team consists of more than 25 traders, marketers and IT professionals that have already created products and services that are being used by millions of people globally.

 Advisors: Lesley O'Neill (https://www.linkedin.com/in/lesleyoneill/) (Binance (https://www.binance.us/)), Arash M. (https://www.linkedin.com/in/arashmahboubi/) (OKX (https://www.okx.com/)), Dyma Budorin (https://twitter.com/buda_kyiv?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor) (Hacken (https://hacken.io/)), Sam E. (https://www.linkedin.com/in/sam-e-434015193/) (GeekCartel (https://www.geekcartel.org/))
 
Partners: Gelato Network (https://www.gelato.network/), HashEx (https://hashex.org/), Zesh.io (http://zesh.io/), Plena.finance (http://plena.finance/), Bridgem.io (http://bridgem.io/), Star.co (http://star.co/), Imem.app (http://star.co/).

metadata.name: Everything Is Real
metadata.bio: “ Everything Is Real" is a series of 9 digital photographs by artist Amber Vittoria. Each photograph contains a sculpture inspired by Vittoria's abstract paintings. These photos break into the notion of what is reality and what is fiction in the rising age of artificial intelligence; they blend the ideas of physical and digital realities and encourage the viewer to question what in their world is indeed real, if not everything?

metadata.name: Everywhere Face Everywhere Noggles
metadata.bio: Everywhere Face Everywhere Noggles" Wherever I find a picture of "look like" a face, I will draw it and put the Noggles there. I see so many "Nouns" objects in this world that resemble faces. So I took a picture and drew Noggles right into a shape that resembled a face.

metadata.name: EVM Explorer

metadata.name: Farcastles
metadata.bio: Farcastles is a collaborative worldbuilding project built natively on Farcaster. On the surface it is a minimum viable game loop with a minimal narrative hook: the castle in the North is at war with the castle in the South. In this community game, hosted on a channel in Farcaster, players roleplay as sell swords in a medieval fantasy universe defending their castle. There are very few rules and the game is mostly about the LARP. However, it also serves as a platform for players to express their creativity through art and storytelling or for builders to create applications on top of it. The game has been a consistent source of fun, collaboration, camaraderie and even rivalries on Farcaster over the last 6 months without ever releasing an official token or introducing any financial elements. The brand and its world belongs to the community of players and channel followers that interact inside it everyday.

metadata.name: Farconic
metadata.bio:
Farconic is an innovative city-building strategy game where players collect NFT cards of iconic buildings from around the world, all designed by the renowned artist Yoni Alter. Whether you prefer to collect these buildings solo as unique artworks or collaborate with friends to assemble entire cities, the game offers a rich, creative experience.

You can work together to establish a city, and once formed, there’s even the potential to elect a mayor who can lead the city’s development. Imagine inviting your friends to live in your city, adding to its vibrancy and value. Yoni Alter’s distinctive style brings each city to life, making each NFT not just a game piece, but a piece of art. For more on Yoni’s work, check out these links:

• https://yonialter.com
• List of select Press Releases on Shapes of Cities: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1r-D5GjFsK6Zr8oeptdwlKU-ZnnxZTzcWJWQx3cOOiPo/edit?usp=sharing
• About the Artist: https://yoniishappy.com/about/

Check out our frames:
• Open a pack of Farconic cards: https://warpcast.com/gilalter.eth/0x621a3b01
• Search through all available cards: https://warpcast.com/gilalter.eth/0xc4834aed
• Buy a Building Card in-frame: https://warpcast.com/gilalter.eth/0x8804eb99
• See the cards you collected on our WebApp: https://farconic.xyz/gallery
• Soon we will release a frame enabling players to collaborate to craft City cards using their Building NFTs!

Onchain Metrics:
• Our project is live on Base. 
• We've had hundreds of mints of our Building Cards NFTs.
• >3k users of our frames, >700 unique: https://airstack.xyz/users/fc_fname%3Aberlin%E2%94%82berlin%E2%94%82farcaster?tab=analytics
• Our /farconic channel has 6'000 members

Note on our Onchain Metrics:
• Due to the nature of our NFTs, onchain metrics might be slightly more difficult to calculate based solely on our mint address.
• Our NFTs are created on bonding curve contracts using the mint.club protocol.
• Each Card has it's own contract address. We're constantly deploying new cards and contracts. 
• Sincerely hope this can be taken into account, or that the evaluation tool is smart enough to detect that our mint wallet has deployed all these contracts.

metadata.name: Feedback Forge - Decentralized Feedback Platform
metadata.bio:
Feedback Forge is a decentralized platform designed to enhance and manage feedback within community-driven projects, leveraging the Optimism ecosystem. Users can provide feedback using a 0-5 star rating system with optional comments. Initially, feedback will be managed via a voting contract where votes are stored in a mapping.

In the future, we plan to introduce a token and ERC-1155 NFTs to gamify and incentivize feedback participation. For instance, users with varying levels of feedback activity will receive evolving NFTs to represent their contributions.

Feedback Forge aims to promote transparency and continuous improvement through blockchain technology, fostering innovation in decentralized feedback mechanisms. Once polished, the platform will drive demand for Optimism blockspace and enhance interactions among users with high trust scores and new users alike.

We are in the early stages of development and welcome your support and feedback as we evolve. Our ultimate goal is to build a gasless solution using innovative verification methods, ensuring seamless user experience.

metadata.name: Founder n Building community - Maskay
metadata.bio:
**What is it about?**

Today we are a *public good*, it is about many things.

The most important thing we do is to be next to the artists so that they can make their art visible, next to their creative process, their art, personally I consider this a very sensitive work, since one knows the artist's reality and how it relates to the ways of making art.

We are also constantly organizing collective drops, incorporating new offchain artists and mixing them with onchain artists.

We curate artworks because we consider this a way of acquiring art from another side, maybe this makes the artworks we collect feel closer to us. We like to be able to promote the artwork and its creator in this way.

We do irls workshops, for training, and debates on web3 where doubts come out, topics about what happens in crypto art, and from where also come out collections and artworks.

**How was it formed?**

It began with the possibility of helping artists from our immediate environment, from Tucumán, from the interior of Argentina and from the peripheries of the country. To be able to make their art visible in the digital world.

Due to the scarce resources for artists in these geographical areas, and the lack of knowledge of digitality and even more of web3, we decided to investigate and train ourselves to make their art visible and help in a possible monetization of theirs works.

metadata.name: Fractal Visions
metadata.bio:
Fractal Visions is an OP centric creator platform for retroactive and quadratic funding on Optimism or Base.

Public goods initiatives from across the planet need more visibility for the intention behind their cause for impact. Audio, Visual, A.i., ReFi, and DeSci projects often have a hard time finding their path in the blockchain space which is why we are here. With the help of Gitcoin grants & the rewards we have received from Retro PGF round 2 and round 3, our core engineer team has contributed to the ecosystem by building the MVP.

The implementation of our own marketplace also intertwines the open source software technology of Allo protocol. Fractal Visions hybrid grants platform for both Retroactive & Quadratic Funding established an independent grants program for Superchain contributors.
Fractal Visions impact initiative platform is utilizing the public goods ethos of Optimism with a retroactive rewards mechanism generated by the marketplace fee from sales to attract authentic creators or developers who are making a significant change with meaningful impact in the real world.

Each artwork is minted as a token on the blockchain and can be uploaded and showcased on platforms supporting Superchain and Optimism.

In addition to the project, we will conduct educational sessions on generative art and blockchain-based tokens in online spaces and educational environments such as Farhous and X. These sessions aim to increase awareness and knowledge about this form of art and tokens. The project seeks to provide an innovative artistic experience while enhancing public understanding of this field.

metadata.name: Gitcoin Citizens Round #1
metadata.bio:
The inaugural Gitcoin Citizens Round, powered by Gitcoin Grants Stack and running on the Optimism network, ran from June 13 – June 27, 2023, employing retroactive QF to reward contributions with proven value to the Gitcoin ecosystem. The round had a matching pool of 20K DAI and has been the most successful round to date in terms of crowdfunding versus matching, having the highest-ever matching pool multiplier with quadruple the available matching funds made in donations. (80K)

Conceptually, running these rounds lowers the barrier of entry for contributing to Gitcoin, determines what the community values most, and helps test (dogfood) the Allo protocol.

Specifically, the three objectives of this experiment were:

1) To gain experience using quadratic funding and the Allo protocol to build our own ecosystem, demonstrate effectiveness, and identify areas for improvement.
2) To experiment with a supplementary budgeting process that has greater accountability and less administrative overhead.
3) To increase community engagement and participation at all levels of Gitcoin from contribution to governance

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: This was a round to reward Gitcoin Citizens for their contributions to the Gitcoin ecosystem

metadata.name: HOMES
metadata.bio:
What are Homes?

Homes by Based Fellas will serve as the staking hub for the 30% of Staking not allocated to Lazy Staking. Based Fellas and similar Base NFTs can be staked into Homes to earn passive tokens while they remain locked. A total of 5,000 Homes will be available in small, medium, or large sizes, referred to as Bungalows, Villas, and Manors.

In each of the 10 Lands of the Legendaries, 500 homes will be present, summing up to 5,000 homes in total.

Bungalows: Small homes capable of housing up to 4 NFTs.

Villas: Medium homes accommodating up to 8 NFTs.

Manors: Large homes with a capacity for up to 12 NFTs.

In each land, there are 275 Bungalows, 150 Villas, and 75 Manors, providing a total of 32,000 spaces for NFTs to reside and receive staking rewards.

This necessitates 30 unique pieces of art from an artist. Across different lands, each sized home will appear fairly similar, with colors and accents distinguishing its location.

name: I just called to say ILY (and more)

metadata.name: I just called to say ILY (and more)
metadata.bio:
Hello there! I'm Ismene. I'm a French visual artist and writer, currently deep into the rabbit hole of AI art (text-to-image, image-to-image, and all the magic in between). You can find me in Tokyo, where I live, or on Farcaster. My art journey started years ago with paper and glue collages. Recently, I've been expressing myself through hand-made digital collage animations and through AI art (via Midjourney,  Emprops and Luma). 

My core inspiration is a mix between surrealism and nostalgia. Crafted with love and art history /pop culture elements.

My main series are titled "I just called to say ILY", "Time flies" (both built through a surrealist conversation with Midjourney about love, longing and nostalgia), "Animée" (a collection of hand-made digital collage animations), and very recently I started "Fabulous beings in their natural habitat" (an animated collection of magnificent 'fab' beings found both via digital collage and AI magic).

My main series are titled "I just called to say ILY", "Time flies" (both built through a surrealist conversation with Midjourney about love, longing and nostalgia), "Animée" (a collection of hand-made digital collage animations), and very recently I started "Fabulous beings in their natural habitat" (an animated collection of magnificent 'fab' beings found both via digital collage and AI magic).

I've been creating and sharing my art on various networks of the Superchain, mainly on Zora and Base, but also on Optimism.

And because art creation goes hand-in-hand with art appreciation, I've been a pretty active collector of other artists' works on the chains mentioned above.

metadata.name: I'm not an AI
metadata.bio:
This is a series of music NFTs created by a fictitious artist named "I'm not an AI," who paradoxically sings "I am not AI" despite being generated through a combination of the music generation AI "Suno" and the image generation AI "Midjourney."
The intention behind this corpus of work is to elucidate the discordance between rapidly evolving AI technologies and the comparatively sluggish adaptation of human cognition and legal frameworks. The progression of technology often ruthlessly overturns established paradigms, repeatedly confronting us with binary choices devoid of unequivocal solutions.
It is the author's fervent aspiration that the poignant outcry of these ephemeral AI entities will resonate with future generations, guiding them towards judicious decision-making in this complex landscape.

metadata.name: Ìtàn African Art Gallery
metadata.bio: LARGEST ONCHAIN CURATIONS OF AFRICAN ART! "Itan" translates to "story" or "history" in Yoruba. Yoruba people are one of the largest and most culturally significant ethnic groups in West Africa. Yoruba culture is known for its vibrant and expressive arts, including sculpture, textiles, music, dance, and storytelling. Yoruba art has a strong emphasis on symbolism and spirituality and has influenced the broader African art world. Itan Foundation World isn’t just about displaying art, but also about telling the stories and histories of West African artists, their cultures and their creative journeys. Each artwork is selected for its ability to evoke a sense of storytelling and exploration.

metadata.name: ItsNaastaaraan
metadata.bio:
Curating Art in Web3: Building a Decentralized Art Gallery"

This project focuses on creating a decentralized art gallery in the Web3 space, where digital art can be curated, exhibited, and sold through the use of blockchain technology. The platform will serve as a curated NFT marketplace, showcasing high-quality digital art from both emerging and established artists. By leveraging the transparency and ownership features of blockchain, the gallery aims to empower artists with greater control over their work while offering collectors a secure and innovative way to discover and purchase art.

The gallery will be governed by a community-driven model, where users can participate in curatorial decisions, ensuring that the platform remains dynamic and inclusive. It will also offer a seamless user experience, with features like virtual galleries, exclusive NFT drops, and a rewards system to engage collectors and art enthusiasts.

The project seeks $250,000 in funding to develop the platform, hire a curatorial team, market the gallery, and build a sustainable ecosystem that supports long-term growth. The ultimate goal is to establish a leading platform in the Web3 space known for its high-quality curation, vibrant community, and commitment to innovation in the art world.

metadata.name: JEFE TOKEN
metadata.bio:
JEFETOKEN is a software development project focused on smart contracts, blockchain technology, video games & mobile applications. Our goal is to create an ecosystem of web3 applications, based on our own token that powers our platforms and services. Additionally, we offer education through interactive workshops, both in-person and digital, to facilitate user integration into the blockchain ecosystem.
Blockchain: The JEFE token is developed Open source under the MIT license,  coded in Solidity and forms the foundation of the project, deployed on the mainnet in Optimism as $JEFE with the vision of being part of the SUPERCHAIN.

Application Development: We implement web3 activities within the community, promoting healthy competition through participation in educational workshops and learning activities on blockchain usage. All information is accessible to users from our website and with direct support on our social media channels. We have our own video game, Jefe Zombie, available on Android and iOS. This game introduces users to using their ERC-20 address to rank within the community and earn on-chain rewards, such as $JEFE & NFTs, and off-chain rewards, such as game appearances & accessories.

Community Support: We also support community talent in areas like sports (American football and paintball), audiovisual art, helping artists transition to the web3 world, and e-sports, promoting competition and game streaming among users.

JEFE University: We have JEFE University, a tour of presentations  and workshops at universities about Optimism, blockchain & web3. We generate POAPs (Proof of Attendance Protocol) for attendees, promoting learning and knowledge sharing. Created JEFE KNUCKLES research & development including a tool for deployment of open source blockchain using Op Stack, collaborating with the governance & education of directives, professors & students from Universities. 

Rewards Program: We incentivize talent and user engagement within our ecosystem through a comprehensive rewards program, prominently featured on our website. Additionally, we're currently developing JEFE COMPASS, an innovative mobile Dapp where users can seamlessly monitor the global community ranking, organize activities, and track both on-chain and off-chain interactions from community addresses and VOTE for events, competitions, top players and more. By participating, users earn rewards points, enabling them to evolve their progress and level of their ranking within the community. 
This program recurrently lists community activities that integrate web3, providing an access point to understand the use case of JEFE TOKEN. We act as a compass for navigating the web3 world, with a vision of a Superchain. Our utility is to support the transition from web2 to its integration with the Superchain in web3 interactively.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: We empower heroes globally, fostering talent and community spirit. As a JEFE in the sports world and beyond, our identity transcends into the local community through web3 technology. We embody the essence of a JEFE in every aspect: from uplifting our neighborhoods to embodying the discipline & resilience of a student athlete warrior to the new generations all in sync within Superchain in mind, soul, body & web3.

- Backed by reputed investors like Sequoia Capital (India), Coinbase Ventures, IOSG, Hashed and more!
- Crossed $16B in trading volume with more than 80k wallets in 7 months of operation with Orderly Network

With its unique features and integrations, calling LogX Pro a “differentiated” offering would be an understatement. It’s arguably the most advanced trading platform you’ll ever use, hands down!

Since our inception, LogX’s mission has been to make the experience of trading on-chain bigger and better than CeFi, and through that onboard CEX users to DEXes. In fact this mission has remained unaltered ever since we wrote about it in our introduction blog in 2023 here: https://flintlabs.medium.com/flint-labs-next-chapter-7e56a87f4f5e

In our 9 months of operation, we have boldly explored various offerings for different trader segments. We identified two primary trader segments: pro traders desiring orderbook functionality and tools, and those seeking a simpler UX for multi-chain exploration. So we built LogX Pro for the former and LogX OG for the latter.

LogX Pro is an Orderbook based Perp Dex built on top of Orderly Network which is live on Optimism Main-net, Arbitrum  and Base Network.

LogX OG is a Perp DEX which is based on our own AMM pools.

*Our Competitive Edge and Uniqueness:*

What makes LogX Pro a superior orderbook DEX?

2 things primarily:

- Carefully designed pro features

- Deep capabilities via external integrations

Pro features:
- Lightning-fast order matching

- Sub-25-milliseconds latency

- The tightest spreads in DeFi, optimizing cost efficiency

- Gasless transactions

- Cross-margin support

- Advanced order types like TWAP, VWAP

- Omnichain deposits, starting with Arbitrum and Optimism

- An Institutional-grade API stack

- On-demand addition of exotic trading pairs

External Integrations:
- Advanced tools to create automated trading strategies based on signals, alerts and algorithms

- Telegram bot integrations

- Autonomous agents for trading bots

- Community-driven trading vaults

*Growth*

LogX has been one of the fastest growing Perp DEXes on superchain networks. We integrated with Orderly Network and since then have been one of the leading DEXes with Orderly
Sharing some metrics for LogX’s performance on the Orderly Network.

- Unique wallet addresses (lifetime): 89,112
- Total trading volume lifetime(Jan-September): $16,118,778,357
- Avg DAU(last 30 days): 755

LogX has also deployed on other superchain networks like Mode Network and has crossed more than $1.5B in trading volume in a span of 4 months on the Mode Network

LogX’s performance on the Orderly Network can be found here: https://dune.com/logx/logx-pro/c993dc04-216e-466e-ba21-207bba8eed8e

The whole premise of LogX is based built upon composability. LogX does not only integrate with other composable protocols, but other protocols can also integrate LogX. Applications like wallets, copy trading platforms, analytics platforms, etc. can find seamless composability with LogX.

This is important to us because LogX would not have existed if not for the composability of other protocols. We owe our existence to it, and want to ensure that other protocols and apps can build on top of LogX to unlock new value props.

metadata.name: LottoPGF
metadata.bio:
LottoPGF is a permissionless protocol to deploy transparent and unmanipulable lotteries for public goods funding on Ethereum.

Lotteries have historically been a great mechanism for funding public goods (from Ancient Rome reparations to public infrastructure after the War of Independence in the US). This capital formation mechanism can be combined with some of the existing resource allocation mechanisms (e.g., QF, RetroPGF, etc.)

To validate the idea and test our contracts, we launched a viral campaign during the initial frames “hype” on farcaster. We developed POWERBALD, a free-to-play lottery in a frame where people could claim free tickets and try their luck in the daily drawing. We gave away multiple millions of $DEGEN as jackpot prizes and grew a [community of over 27,000 lottery](https://warpcast.com/lottopgf) enthusiasts. 
With our PowerBALD lotteries, we raised $1,500 to co-sponsor a Giveth QF round and are currently integrating with [Zuzalu.city](http://zuzalu.city/) to raise funds for their initiatives.

The PowerBALD Lottery contract was deployed at `0xc94e65A6d6C145B6A0342dA9b5e8Dc3928505857` through our `LooteryFactory` at `0xdED85d9e814c4C23D2632511d3Be9aC4e49524b0`. All relevant contracts are verified on Etherscan and available on our Github.

To play for free, players had to pass sybil checks like having a $DEGEN tip allowance (see https://www.degen.tips/faq) or owning the (now deprecated) active status on farcaster. After passing the requirements, following @lottopgf and liking the cast, the player would be able to choose their numbers and claim a free ticket every day.
Our deployer account at `0x77769134B8181e7eb4462D565BF362eC63A4f12d` would then mint the ticket with the chosen numbers for this user via the `ownerPick` method on the contract, resulting in 23,789 transactions minting 32,150 ticket NFTs for nearly 10,000 unique players. In total, we spent well over 2 ETH on gas fees for free claims on Base pre-4844.

We had to choose the owner transaction variant instead of letting users execute their own transactions as user-initiated transactions were not available in the first version of farcaster frames specs, and additionally executing a transaction free of charge for the user makes for a much more seamless experience.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: LottoPGF incentivizes donations with lottery mechanics

metadata.name: Merkl
metadata.bio:
Merkl is a platform that simplifies the management and distribution of onchain incentives within DeFi ecosystems. By providing a transparent and efficient infrastructure, Merkl empowers protocols, chains, and projects to seamlessly execute large-scale liquidity campaigns, ensuring rewards are distributed fairly and without friction.

In the Superchain ecosystem, Merkl played a crucial role in driving liquidity growth and incentivization across OP Mainnet, Base, Mode, and Fraxtal during the Superfest event. By providing the tools to coordinate incentives across these chains, Merkl significantly boosted liquidity deposits and user engagement in liquidity pools and lending markets. Through Superfest, Merkl efficiently managed the allocation of 1.5 million $OP tokens across these four Superchain blockchains, ensuring rewards were fairly and transparently distributed across 55 liquidity pools and lending markets. This positioned Superfest as a major liquidity driver within the ecosystem.

Disclaimer: We previously received payment from the Optimism Collective for managing Superfest. However, we are re-applying due to our broader contributions to the Superchain ecosystem and our eagerness to expand our impact by integrating additional Superchain networks.

metadata.name: Metronome
metadata.bio:
Metronome is a new DeFi synthetics ecosystem that has both innovated and iterated upon what existed prior in the decentralized synthetic space, creating a secure, user friendly dApp, where users are able to supercharge their yield generation and trade crypto assets in a capital efficient manner.  Metronome has three main components:  Synth, Marketplace, and Smart Farming.

Metronome Synth: Where users can deposit collateral, mint synthetics, and manage their positions.  While similar to other synthetic applications, Metronome Synth separates itself from other products by allowing users to deposit multiple forms of collateral, including yield bearing productive collateral such as LST’s and Vesper Pool share tokens, which act as singular source of collateral value that users can then mint a variety of ever expanding synthetic assets from.  

Metronome Marketplace:  The Marketplace is a synthetic DEX, where users can swap between synthetic assets with zero slippage and low fees.  Through Synth and the Marketplace, users are able to place directional trades on popular crypto assets.  DEX aggregators can also route trades through the marketplace to find the best prices on exotic assets, in a capital efficient manner.

Smart Farming: A yield looping engine that routes through Metronome Synth and Vesper Finance yield strategies.  Smart Farming is the backbone of Metronome, enabling users to effortlessly loop their collateral for increased yield up to 5x.  Through Smart Farming, Metronome is able to offer users industry leading APYs, while maintaining sustainable yield.

metadata.name: Mismir
metadata.bio:
Mismir is a project that I started a while ago, before even discovering the world of Web3, let alone the Superchain. Mismir is a fashion brand that aims to help people express themselves more, feel empowered, empower others, and connect more with one another and themselves.
Each garment of the brand will be chipped, with the chips containing the true value of the piece of clothing. The NFC chips serve as a bridge between the physical and digital worlds, the latter being mostly active on-chain as we have NFTs, POAPs, and soon other elements to be added that will live on-chain. Not all of them can be added on-chain for now, but most of them will.
Currently, as the tangible garments are still under production, I am trying with Mismir to make our presence felt within the on-chain world. We are actively expressing ourselves on Farcaster and Lens, occasionally having our manifestations minted on platforms like Zora and chains like Base. The reason for not moving fully to Zora with our content, and preferring to alternate with Lens, is that we believe in diversity and in the future that Lens is creating for brands like ours, artists, builders, and curators.
Within the brand's ecosystem, there is a series called Storied Strokes which celebrates the transformative power of artistry and the vibrant voices shaping our world. We are taking the voices and stories of artists, turning them into articles, and through the platform we've built thus far, we are spreading them into the world. The main reason is to empower the artists who bring so much good to our lives. The interviews are first posted on Mirror, where we are leveraging the power of the blockchain to ensure that these articles can live on forever, and then on our website, where they can be accessible to more people who are not familiar with or who are skeptical about the on-chain world. We are using the Optimism chain to have our articles minted on-chain!

name: Mt. Fuji / Matsumoto Castle - Half Frame 35mm

metadata.name: Mt. Fuji / Matsumoto Castle - Half Frame 35mm
metadata.bio: Japan is one of my favorite places in the world for many reasons. One thing that always fascinates me are the extreme dualities you find in life and culture there. Ancient & future, modesty & flamboyance, extreme sexuality & repression, bureaucracy & magic. While shooting with my half frame camera on tour I caught this pair of photos. Mt. Fuji from the back yard of a small farm house bathed in the light of a beautiful day, and Matsumoto castle shaded in the darkness of rain clouds. The duality in the shots felt right in line with the extremes you find in Japanese life.

metadata.name: My Truth, My Vision, My Art
metadata.bio:
"My Truth, My Vision, My Art" is an immersive project exploring the intersection of spirituality, identity, and digital existence. Over six months, it has evolved into a digital diary reflecting a continuous journey of self-exploration and creation.

From its inception, the project has focused on building images and decentralized protocols, documenting a series of experiments and discoveries. Through a flow of creations, including images, videos, and animations, it showcases significant progression in color and emotional expression, symbolizing the artist’s personal and artistic evolution.

"My Truth, My Vision, My Art" is more than a collection of works; it’s a testament to an ongoing artistic and technological journey, engaging directly with digital communities through NFTs. The project will culminate in a special event on September 22, featuring a physical exhibition of the works and celebrating the transformation and innovation achieved during these intense months of creation.

metadata.name: ＡＺＵＲＥ
metadata.bio:
Polygon1993's latest piece ａｚｕｒｅ explores themes of loneliness, depression, loss of loved ones, and mental fragility.
Using his signature technique of circuit-bent video synths CRT TVs and digital glitch art, Polygon1993 creates glitch art portraits of people that are made entirely of lines.
This piece is a haunting and abstract representation of his subject's emotional state. The glitchy, fragmented lines that make up each portrait are a reflection of the turmoil and confusion that comes with mental illness.
Through his use of glitch art and technology, Polygon1993 invites us to contemplate the complex emotions that we all experience at some point in our lives.
This unique and powerful depiction of the human experience serves as a testament to the resilience and strength that we can all find within ourselves in the face of adversity.
By using only lines, Polygon1993 creates a sense of depth and movement that draws the viewer in and invites them to explore the intricacies of the artwork.

metadata.name: Newnow World
metadata.bio:

Is a platform designed to facilitate the buying and selling of cryptocurrencies, focusing on the Cuban community. Its goal is to provide easy and secure access to cryptocurrencies, allowing users to conduct transactions efficiently.

Key Features:
Accessibility: The platform is designed to be user-friendly, even for those with no prior experience in cryptocurrencies.

Security:  implements advanced security measures to protect transactions and user data.

Education: It offers educational resources about cryptocurrencies, helping users better understand the market and make informed decisions.

Community: It fosters an active community where users can share experiences, tips, and strategies regarding cryptocurrency use.

Local Support: Considering the Cuban context,  provides customer support in Spanish and tailored to local needs.

By positioning itself as a pioneering solution for cryptocurrency access, Newnow World not only meets the specific needs of the Cuban community but also plays a crucial role in advancing financial literacy and innovation.

metadata.name: NFT HOOK
metadata.bio:
Our team, a dedicated group of Web3 enthusiasts, embarked on our journey into the NFT space driven by our passion for the technology. However, the high cost of early NFTs was a significant barrier to widespread adoption. Discovering Optimistic Layer 2 (OP L2) was a game-changer for us. It enabled us to issue affordable NFTs at a fraction of the cost, opening the door for a broader audience.

This strategic pivot to L2 was met with remarkable success. We have issued millions of NFTs, democratizing access to digital assets. Our most popular NFT boasts over 100,000 holders, a testament to our approach of making NFTs accessible and valuable across multiple blockchains.

Our vision is to continue this trajectory, enhancing the utility and engagement of our NFTs. We are committed to innovating and expanding the functionalities of our NFTs, ensuring they offer more than just ownership—creating new ways for holders to interact with and benefit from their digital assets.

metadata.name: "NOCTURNAL SOLITUDES"
metadata.bio: "In the solitary nights, in the tranquility of the dark night, our minds let go and seek pleasant rest and serenity. Once again, the hidden and profound forces of our minds appear and remove the mask of truth.  In these solitudes, we initiate imagination and deep thinking. We may be looking for meaning and purpose in life, or delve into spirituality and soul-searching. Philosophy helps us ask bigger questions in our quest to understand the world and existence.  In the search for answers and deep meanings, in these solitudes, we find ourselves in a magical connection with our essence. There, we become more familiar with the language of the heart and the unspoken language and establish a connection with our inner silence.  In the nocturnal solitudes, the light of our souls blossoms in the darkness, and we engage in the occupation of becoming better human beings. In this renewed view of the world, we may see fresh, beautiful, and inspiring landscapes.  Let's make use of the nocturnal solitudes to advance our spiritual evolution and gain more insight and awareness of ourselves and the world."  We delve into a deeper world, seeking feedback from true existence. Hidden within us are the big questions to understand the meaning of existence, truth, and justice. In this philosophical journey, our minds grow more than ever, and our eyes gaze at the stars of knowledge and wisdom.  But often, the destruction of our perspectives follows. Where is the guarantee of the right path? Is it within ourselves or in others? Should we connect with others or commit suicide in solitude? The things we seek refuge in inherently lack meaning, and in the external world, we think most of the time about the stories of the sun worshipers and the ash worshipers.  With forms and sufferings, joys and sorrows, we reach the breadth and bounty of experience in the solitude of the night. We become prey turned butterfly, penetrating through a thread of fiery red initiative.  And in the end, in complete sobriety, we rise and discover the eight knots. Each sitting and brief reflects an extraordinary world, the salt ruling over all aspects of existence, and the honey-hearted reminder.  In search of a deeper meaning and harmony with being, we join the true awareness in the final wave of the night from the solitude to the reality, mapping artistic depictions with enthusiasm and profound monasticism. ✨🌌🔍🌟🎨🧘‍♂️" ✨ Digital painting 🖼️  procreate 🖌️ 5000 x 6000 px

metadata.name: Nouns Esports
metadata.bio:
Nouns Esports, one of North America's premier esports teams, is funded by NounsDAO, a leading DAO on the Ethereum network. The organization believes that DAOs offer a superior coordination layer for cultural initiatives like esports. By focusing on onboarding and creating on-chain identities for fans, Nouns Esports empowers its community to actively participate in team governance, fostering deeper engagement and a stronger sense of fandom.

In 2024, Nouns Esports has established itself as the number one North American Dota 2 team and expanded its presence across multiple titles, including Counter-Strike (with both male and female teams), Smash Bros. Melee, and Pokémon UNITE. The organization has also launched Nouns.GG, which has replaced Prop House as the primary platform for esports enthusiasts, tournament organizers, and artists to secure funding for their work.
