metadata.name: Onchain Affiliates
metadata.bio:
Onchain Affiliates is a blockchain-based affiliate marketing program that allows users to earn cryptocurrency and engagement points through social media activities. The project focuses on three main aspects:

Register: Users can easily join the program by connecting their Ethereum-based wallet.
Cast: Participants share affiliate mint frames on social media platforms.
Earn: Users receive ETH commissions for referred mints and points for engagement with their affiliate frames.

The project's roadmap includes four phases:

Launch of the Affiliate Frame & Points System with the Based Gloomers Collection
Addition of features like mint notification bots
Onboarding of other projects and creators
Expansion to integrate other social media platforms

Onchain Affiliates aims to provide a seamless way for influencers and content creators to monetize their engagement and unlock their influence in the blockchain space.

name: Onchain Blobs - Randomly generated onchain blobs minted via a Farcaster frame

metadata.name: Onchain Blobs - Randomly generated onchain blobs minted via a Farcaster frame
metadata.bio:
Hi, I'm Apex a builder on Base, I focus primarily on Onchain NFT's. Notably, the Onchain Dinos, Based Onchain Punks and RAWR 404 token. 

To celebrate the launch of EIP-4844 launching blobs on L2 rollup's across Base, OP, Zora. I deployed a fun onchain collection via a warpcast "mint in frame". 

NFT Details:
- Infinite supply
- Completely stored onchain on Base
- Randomly generated and created using svg reacts and live blockchain data
- Minted via a Warpcast in frame tx build using frogs.fm

Launched on Warpcast on the same day as blobs going live, Onchain blobs quickly trended farcaster, seeing over 6,000 mints from 2800 unique addresses.

metadata.bio: Onchain Mecha is an innovative, Manga inspired, fully-onchain, SVG NFT trading card project. It's art revolves around a short narrative involving Aku, an antagonist attempting universal domination by suppressing creativity to establish supremacy. The story unfolds with 7 unconventional human characters merging symbiotically with 7 ethereal light-created mechas. Together, they combat Aku to safeguard the creative essence maintaining universal balance.. In a magnificent battle they create a unified energy field and split Aku into 7 diluted versions of evil and fling him across the farthest spectrums of the universe. Unfortunately to prevent Aku from reforming himself they must sacrifice and split themselves across the universe as well.

metadata.name: Onchain Metaverse Adventures
metadata.bio:
🚀 I embarked on a transformative adventure, diving headfirst into the Metaverse and Web3, and I'm taking you all with me! From setting up my first social accounts in both Web2 and Web3 realms to entering the grandest onchain art contest with prizes totaling over 1.2 million OP, this video is a rollercoaster of creativity, innovation, and digital entrepreneurship.

In this vlog, I share everything:

My leap into the massive on-chain art contest "We Love The Art" by Optimism. 🎨

My deep dive into Ethscription, featuring a groundbreaking NFT collection that's traded over $1.8M in just 30 days. 💼

The creation of my first-ever NFT music video using Unreal Engine, revealing the secrets behind my digital art. 🎬

The secrets to my whopping 2000% profit in less than two weeks with the groundbreaking $DEGEN social token. 💹

metadata.name: Onchain
metadata.bio:
ONCHAIN is an anthem of decentralization, innovation, and freedom, celebrating the builders who challenge traditional systems and embrace a future of collaboration and transparency.

"ONCHAIN" was born out of our fascination with blockchain technology. We see its potential to transform industries and liberate individuals from traditional systems. The song is a reflection of our journey and our beliefs – it’s about freedom, innovation, and collaboration. We wanted to capture the excitement and possibilities that come with decentralization and digital freedom.

Creating the music video was an adventure in itself! We had countless brainstorming sessions, coming up with wild concepts that brought out our collective creativity. One of my most memorable moments was recording "ONCHAIN" in the studio. The energy was electric, and it felt like all our hard work had paid off. Seeing our vision come to life was magical.

Recently, my band and I had the incredible opportunity to be featured on "IN THE META with Mia" from Metaverse University TV. We got to talk about our latest track, "ONCHAIN," and give you a behind-the-scenes look at the music video creation process. It was an absolute blast! 

Check out the full interview on Zora: 
https://zora.co/collect/base:0xdf0d0e93672111a3e52e7765d38b7a1ccf165f7a/1

name: Onchainomics Essay #1 'Introduction to Onchainomics: ​ Shaping the Future of Borderless Economy'​

metadata.name: Onchainomics Essay #1 'Introduction to Onchainomics: ​ Shaping the Future of Borderless Economy'​
metadata.bio: Onchainomics, a portmanteau of the terms "on-chain" and "economics," aims to raise attention to the study of emerging economic activities taking place on blockchain networks, and how these on-chain activities impact the IRL global economy.

name: Onchainomics Essay #2 'Bridging Onchainomics with Decentralised Social: a Social Platform, or an Emerging Re-globalisation Society'

metadata.name: Onchainomics Essay #2 'Bridging Onchainomics with Decentralised Social: a Social Platform, or an Emerging Re-globalisation Society'
metadata.bio: The Onchainomics Essay #2 'Bridging Onchainomics with Decentralised Social: a Social Platform, or an Emerging Re-globalisation Society' is an award-winning essay, which has won the 2nd prize in the t2 x Kiwi x Lens Writing Contest on 19 July 2024. This paper explores the potential of intersecting traditional economics with the emerging topic of DeSoc and discovers the calculation and definition of on-chain GDP and consumption.

metadata.name: Orderly Network
metadata.bio:
Orderly Network is a combination of an orderbook-based trading infrastructure and a robust liquidity layer offering perpetual futures. Unlike traditional platforms, Orderly doesn’t have a front end; instead, it operates at the core of the ecosystem, providing essential services to projects built on top of it.

Built on top of the OP Stack, Orderly Chain settles trades across multiple blockchains leveraging its asset management vaults for user deposits. These asset vaults are currently deployed across Arbitrum, OP Mainnet, Base, Polygon POS and Mantle. 

Orderly has 12 brokers built on top of its infrastructure currently - 11/12 of these are deployed to the OP and Base mainnet asset vaults. These brokers/projects include WOOFi Pro, LogX, SharpeAI, Bitoro, EMDX, Ascendex, CoolWallet and more. Orderly has an additional 10+ projects in the "integration underway" stage and/or on testnet to deploy in the coming months. 

Details on Orderly OP Stack can be found on our explorer: 
https://explorer.orderly.network/

Orderly overall TVL: $38.5m
TVL Breakdown in OP & Base - 
Optimism Mainnet TVL: $8,608,017
Base TVL: $1,348,071

Up to date statistics can be found at: 
https://dune.com/orderly_network/orderly-dashboard

Team Members and Roles: 45+ Team members across 10+ countries.
Core contributors: Ran (CEO), Terence (CTO), Arjun (COO), Bryan (Product), Slava (Product), Amine (Product), Midoji (BD & Product), Aurora (BD), Henry (Institutional BD), Drew (Marketing), Brandon (Social & Content Marketing), Irene (Growth Marketing)

metadata.name: Peapods Finance
metadata.bio:
Peapods introduces a new concept called ‘Volatility Farming’; the ability to tokenize the volatile price movements of any liquid token, and return them as yield to protocol stakeholders by creating and capitalizing on arbitrage opportunities. 

Peapods works by wrapping one or more tokens into a Pod [vault], and creating a synthetic Pod receipt token that is made liquid via an incentivised liquidity pool. The Pod receipt is always redeemable for its vault tokens, and therefore arbitrage opportunities occur whenever the liquid Pod price deviates from its net asset value. Yield is generated by imposing wrap and unwrap fees on bots through the monopolized arbitrage path.

Every aspect of Peapods is composable and permissionless.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: Peapods introduces a fundamentally novel DeFi primitive. We are the first 'Volatility Farming' protocol, leveraging volatility and arbitrage as a sustainable source of real yield for any liquid token..

name: ‘Quote Your Summer Art’ - collective drop by the quote-art channel community.  Concept and organizing: V5MT

metadata.name: Quote Your Summer Art - collective drop by the quote-art channel community
metadata.bio:
'Quote Your Summer Art' is the first collective drop by the quote-art channel community on Warpcast, conceptualized, curated, and organized by me (V5MT). It was fully released on July 18th as a collection on the Zora platform, offering free-to-mint editions on the Base network. The collection features artworks from 18 artists, including the GIF art legend Francoise Gamma and other well-known artists in the NFT space. I aimed to ensure the selection of artists was as gender-balanced as possible, with a particular focus on including women artists, which I successfully achieved. The collection is also aesthetically diverse, reflecting the versatile techniques and styles of the selected artists.
I set up the Warpcast quote-art channel on April 9th at the request of the artist Trapers, who wanted to create a channel inspired by the art quoting trend of sharing one's own art based on a given theme. The channel quickly attracted a growing community of some of the best artists, inspiring me to organize a collective drop featuring the most frequent quote-art users.
For the first drop, I chose the theme 'Quote Your Summer Art' to celebrate the joy of summertime through creativity and collaboration, embracing the spirit of the on-chain summer movement. My goal is to gradually feature all the best artists active in the channel in future themed collective drops.
I hope these drops will bring more attention and support to the quote-art artists.
◆◆◆ Theme: 'Quote Your Summer Art' ◆ Concept, organizing, promo: V5MT ◆ Release date: July 18th ◆ Platform: zora.co ◆ Network: Base ◆ Edition: Open, time-limited, free-to-mint ◆ Featured Artists: Francoise Gamma, La Delmas, Trapers, p.i.x.e.l.l.a.r.e., Zaaa Bey, Tornado Rodriguez, desultor, Isa Kost, 1mposter, Riniifish, MEKAZOO, nasty-stz, bluretina, Nadie, stulka, Louis16art, se.nao.maya, V5MT.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: With this project, I focused on community building and organization. This included conceptualizing the idea, selecting the artists for the drop, managing the entire process from start to release, and communicating with the artists in the 'quote-your-art-drops' group chat I set up on Warpcast. I also promoted the drop intensively through flyers, videos, and casts that I created. My goal was to cultivate collaboration among talented artists, build a supportive community, and ensure the success and visibility of the drop within the NFT space.

metadata.name: Quote Your Touch-Grass Art - collective drop by the quote-art channel community
metadata.bio:
Quote Your Touch-Grass Art is the upcoming second collective drop by the quote-art channel community on Warpcast, conceptualized, curated, and organized by me (V5MT). The drop is planned for release on September 20th and features 20 artists from the most frequent contributors to the 'quote-art' channel. Some are featured again, including the legend Francoise Gamma, while the majority are newly invited. The selection process also aimed to achieve a gender balance, with a strong representation of women artists.
For this drop, I chose the theme 'Quote Your Grass-touch Art' to bring some nature onchain and maintain the onchain summer spirit. I asked the artists to interpret the theme in their usual style, but with at least some touch of green to visually tie the collection together. All the artworks are still in the making. 
My goal is to gradually feature all the best artists active in the channel in future themed collective drops. I hope these drops will bring more attention and support to the quote-art artists."
■■■ About quote-art channel:■■■ 
The quote-art channel was the idea of artist trapers, who noticed the art quoting trend on Warpcast and wanted to start a dedicated channel. He asked me to set it up, which I did on April 9th. Since then, we’ve been co-moderating the channel together, having fun and keeping it growing every day. We were thrilled to see it attract a community of top-notch artists using it daily for art sharing and fun theme-chains. This inspired me to organize a series of collective drops featuring the most active “quoters.” This is the second edition.
──⬥──

My goal is to cultivate collaboration among talented artists, build a supportive community, and ensure the drop's success and visibility within the NFT space.

metadata.name: re-frame
metadata.bio:
This generative artwork is using the copyright-free, CC0-licensed collection data of the Finnish National Gallery in its implementation. Two search queries are used while interacting with the database: landscape and still life. These concepts are historically entangled with artistic practice, where the author aims to interpret different psychological, emotional or other phenomena through the built and the natural environment. Working with collection data, it is not possible to show the physical artworks in their originality, thus re-frame takes an approach of turning computational space into a metaphysical environment by combining a landscape with a still life from different authors into new combinations, resulting in a hybrid, multidimensional area of outdoor, indoor, mental and associative locations.

The title and short description of each iteration is generated by combining the available metadata of the selected artworks. Where there is no English translation available, re-frame defaults back to the original Finnish expressions, resulting in a hybrid, unconventional language, specific to the dataset.

metadata.name: Scoop3
metadata.bio:
Scoop3 is an onchain podcast player built on the Degen network which is under the Base chain. I believe we are the first crypto media app operating on an L3. We opted for an L3 because of the minuscule minting fees which we think are going to be necessary to scale. 
Podcast listeners want to signal their fandom, and they can do so by listening to podcasts, and getting an NFT of the podcast they just listened to. On the other side of the equation, podcasters want to know who their fans are and be able to recognize them (however they want), and podcast NFTs allow them to do that.
Essentially, we are bringing fans and creators are closer together. 

Couple notes:
* We have a patent-pending process which tokenizes media seamlessly, so the podcaster does NOT have to be crypto savvy to use the platform. This is our secret sauce.
* We DO have a working app currently on Testflight that our angel investors are using. We will be rolling it out to more people in the near future.

At the end of everyday, creators on Farcaster are ranked by their engagement score (likes, new follows etc). The owners of the top ranking cards receive rewards (proportional to their ownership) from the community pool — the better your creator does on farcaster, the more you earn.

Farcaster creators earn a cut of every trade that happens on their profile.

metadata.name: song.camp: mint your music
metadata.bio:
We created song.camp as a chill place that puts music nft's first. Song.camp is a simple instance of Zora that allows users to post, mint and share music on Base. Its distinct features are that of a persistent music player that allows you to stream songs as you navigate around the site, as well as an incredibly simple Create flow that abstracts away all token parameters from the creator.

When a song is posted through our app, a new Zora contract on Base is automatically created under the hood with Token ID 1 as that song. A 30-day open edition mint priced at the Zora Mint Fee is also initiated. This allows musicians to simply upload their music, cover artwork, song name and hit create - that’s it! Our minimal UI’s design also allows the music and its cover artwork to have center stage. We’ve created super sleek and simple standalone mint pages for each song, making it all about the music and cover art. Finally, our app has minting and commenting integrated natively, so don’t forget to $enjoy!

metadata.name: Spector Release Campaign
metadata.bio:
This summer I'm building a world around my latest single, Spector. The reason I am doing this is because I want to break from the "norm" of the music industry (i.e. focus on streaming, 6-week release schedule, once a song is out onto the next forget about the last). People only share the final product in music (ie: the song) but never the process behind it, why certain decisions were made, and how/why the song was made. 

For Spector, I'm sharing everything along the journey and minting them on Base. Not just the art but my thoughts and feelings as the song developed, also including rare artefacts created during the campaign that wouldn't normally be shared. This then gives collectors an insight into my process and procedures for releasing music. Target audience for the audio is fans of electronic music but by sharing the story of the release, the aim is to reach music fans globally regardless of musical genre preference. 

All the videos of the project are being minted on Zora as free + protocol rewards open edition mints. The song itself is minted on Sound as a free + protocol rewards open edition. This makes all aspects of the campaign collectible and accessible at an affordable price. 

This has been a fun experiment approaching a release campaign at a different angle and documenting the process onchain.

metadata.name: Start Mode : Summer 2024
metadata.bio:
Start Mode began on Farcaster as my first channel, focusing on the appreciation and support for gaming, art, and culture through experiential projects. It is the beginning of bringing more diverse mindsets on the superchain to share/discuss game-inspired creativity and methodologies in the artistic process. 

To start, I developed my own art project for OnChain Summer 2024 on Zora via the Base Blockchain. "Start Mode: Summer 2024" is a diverse set of animated artworks that evolve into various character sets through machine learning. Each piece is unique and shows love for the past, present, and future of pixel art. The functionality of this collection is similar to the concept of Pokemon, with each animation minted evolving into the next one. I used RunwayML, Touch Designer, and Photomosh to help develop these surreal posthumanistic figures. 

As a result, it gained a lot of great traction within the community. As only 17 artworks exist in this collection, over 140 mints supported this collection.

It is the first step into Start Mode's world, and it brings more conversations around gaming, art, and diverse cultures together.

The central focus is a red figure, lovingly depicted by Lena as her father. Although simple in form, this figure radiates warmth and closeness, capturing the affection Lena feels for her dad.

metadata.name: Superchain Safe
metadata.bio:
Safe (formerly Gnosis Safe) is the most secure and trusted smart-contract wallet available across 80+ EVM networks, with over $150B+ in total value locked (TVL). In addition to its widely-used multi-signature functionality, Safe’s modular architecture offers exceptional customization (e.g., native account abstraction support) and integration capabilities (such as direct connectivity with DApps and Protocols), making Safe not just a wallet, but a comprehensive platform for managing funds.

Superchain Safe is a platform that integrates Safe's solutions across 10+ networks within the Superchain ecosystem. It provides a unified interface for managing funds across all networks in one place. Protofire DAO manages and supports the Superchain Safe instance, continuously adding new networks and expanding its features, including Safe Apps, Modules, Guards, and Wallet Integrations.

Superchain Safe is crucial not only for end users - such as DAOs, DApps, Protocols, and Investors - but also for the entire ecosystem, as its components form an essential part of the infrastructure. Overall, Superchain Safe plays a key role in driving Superchain adoption, enhancing security and reliability, and increasing TVL across all Superchain networks.

For creatives venturing into the onchain ecosystem, the importance of tools that guarantee provenance, help with distribution, and provide a pleasant user experience (UX/UI) cannot be overstated. These tools are crucial for ensuring that artists and creators can effectively manage and distribute their work, maintain its authenticity, and engage with their audience in meaningful ways.

The ecosystem is being designed to create new landing spots for non-builders to empower creators and normal users with safe spaces to explore, learn, commune, and commerce. metadata.name: Symbolic Citees
metadata.bio: Anemale is an artistic project by two artists. In 2023, we created a collection called Symbolic Citees, inspired by generative art assembled layer by layer for visual and symbolic coherence. We have created more than 1850 Symbolic CITEES, drawing inspiration from cinema, history, science, technology, mythology, fantasy, video games, and certain artists that we particularly appreciate such as Yves Klein, Dali, Kenda, Cocteau, Burton, Chagall, Miyazaki, Matisse, Gericault, as well as collections like Squiggles, Fidenza or Autoglyph. The mint is currently in progress on Foundation, but we couldn't modify the mint price and ETH has doubled in price since the start of our project, so this collection was doomed to fail. However, thanks to Base, we have built an incredible community with over 8k followers on Warpcast. We have made incredible connections and set up a subscription on Hypersub, which allows our collectors to subscribe for 1 or several months. Each month, our subscribers receive 1 drop of a City per day. Our artistic project has come back to life, and our community is growing day by day to reveal this magnificent collection.

metadata.name: The Magic Machine
metadata.bio:
Based on the Tezos Art Vending Machine Project "The Magic Machine" aims to solve some of the most important problems in the current onchain art scene. Helping artists and users in the same time. With the focus on discovering, curation and distribution, the Magic Machine provides artists with a way to distribute their artworks to a selected audience and collectors with new high quality artworks in a couple of clicks.

Creators flow
· Create.
· Send artwork to the machine.
· Enjoy.

Collectors flow
· Click the "Find Art" button in the machine frame.
· Choose a chain and a payment method. Confirm.
· Get random high quality artworks in their wallets.

what does mean for creators and collectors?
We provide artists a new way to increase their exposure with no effort through our innovative system of distribution and we also are in charge of curating the artworks providing our users only high quality artworks saving tons of gold (time) for all of them.

For creators this means that they can focus on creating high quality art while the Magic Machine is in charge of randomly distributing it to a selected audience in the Farcaster network. Freeing them of the struggle to fight againts others artists for a bit of attention. With the Magic Machine, the attention of collectors is fairly distributed between all the artists and artworks contributing to the protocol ensuring that all of them remains visible to collectors.

Currently collectors have to spend their attention, time and effort, scrolling through tons of low effort art. With the Magic Machine, collectors only need about 1 minute to discover and collect 3 new high quality artworks. Giving them the rest of the day, about 86340 seconds, to do whatever they want to do.

In the future, a reward mechanism based on points could also help with engagement, offering loyal users and artists a way to extract the maximum value for their contributions.

metadata.name: The Mercenary Mafia

It builds on the game of Farcastles adding an extra layer of depth and nuance giving players away to level up and gain rank within this new faction or "Family" without changing the base layer of play. Members of the Mercenary Mafia can conduct attacks for the family and anyone of the 6 crews using an emoji-herald identifier that will log their attacks and distribute points accordingly. Once the first version of the frame is ready players will be able to check their profile, see an attack history, their total damage they have dealt within their Mafia career and their level and rank. Players will also be able to see a leaderboard of the top 20 hitters and crews. Its a fun project that is been done with no funding.

metadata.name: The Optimism Show
metadata.bio:
The Optimism Show starts as a podcast on covering the business landscape of the Optimism Superchain from a non-technical perspective. The goal of the Optimism Show is to twofold:
1. To provide valuable, actionable, and real-world business insights to founders on the Optimism Superchain
2. To educate and inform non-web3 founders and investors about the Optimism Superchain in a simplified and non-technical way. To present them the actual picture from a non-developer perspective and to show the opportunity in the Optimism Superchain.

The ultimate goal is to bring more people on the superchain that want to build cool stuff with cool people.

To date:
The show was launched on the 19th of September 2024, and for a start will be promoting the Optimism Ecosystem with the following media:
- 2 Weekly episodes with major founders on the Optimism Superchain
- 15 to 25 weekly promotional reels
- 2 weekly newsletters

In the works:
- Monthly/Bi-weekly networking events (virtual, and in-person in Italy and the Balkan Peninsula). Partnership already established with a music event organizer.

Coverage on:
- YouTube
- Drakula (Farcaster client)
- Instagram
- TikTok
- All major podcasting platforms

metadata.name: TOCD Studio
Token Engineering Commons
metadata.bio: The Token Engineering Commons (TEC) is a DAO on the OP chain, committed to fostering the development of trustworthy and sustainable token economies. Its mission is to help establish a new engineering discipline that blends the principles, tools, and practices of traditional engineering with the design of cryptoeconomic systems. The TEC achieves this by promoting awareness and education around token engineering, while also offering grants and other opportunities to support projects that empower individuals and teams to innovate and advance the field.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: As our primary focus is to provide support to the token engineering community through our grants program, we believe this category is the best fit for us.   Our main contributions have been centered around our grant program, utilizing the Gitcoin Protocol to distribute funds to Token Engineering projects within the OP ecosystem. Since the Beta Round, we have been repeatedly selected as a community round by Gitcoin, showcasing our experience and the significant impact we've made in both the token engineering and public goods space, as well as within the Superchain ecosystem. To date, we have successfully conducted three QF rounds in OP, committing over $100k to the OP ecosystem and supporting more than 30 projects. Our latest round was the only one to focus exclusively on Superchain ecosystem projects and utilized an innovative on-chain mechanism—Tunable Quadratic Funding (TQF)—which boosted donation matching from donors with onchain signals that signaled ecosystem expertise (badge holders, delegates, and $OP token holders). This approach optimizes funding allocation to better align with the goals and needs of the OP ecosystem.  As we continue to see the evolution of our grant program, we continue to place a focus on refining our selection processes to identify projects that demonstrate strong or high potential for impact. This includes enhancing our criteria, selection methods, evaluation processes, and providing ongoing support to maximize each project’s potential.  We continue to build towards a continued impact in the OP ecosystem by connecting OP projects with reputable Token Engineering resources such as the Token Engineering Academy and TE consulting groups. We believe our impact to date, and future impact will be significant.  Thank you for your time and consideration.

metadata.name: Trash NFTs
metadata.bio:
Trash NFTs is a project built on Base that leverages the unique properties of the ERC404 token standard. We had the idea for Trash NFTs as a way to combine artichokelord’s incredible artwork with novel tech to create something fun that pushed the boundaries of what’s possible for a memecoin. We chose to build Trash NFTs on Base because we believe in the future of the Superchain and the supportive community of builders it fosters.

Between the two contracts associated with Trash NFTs, the project has generated over 1300 onchain transactions.

Demo video: https://youtu.be/KORe_xnJx1w?si=6V52TlkOfLz3hySz
Video of artichokelord drawing the art: https://warpcast.com/trashnfts/0xc65d2a4e

ERC404 is an experimental token standard pioneered by Pandora on February 2, 2024. ERC404 tokens embrace characteristics of both ERC20 and ERC721 tokens: They are “semi-fungible,” enabling both highly liquid markets and uniqueness within a single asset. This allows collectors to sell their tokens when they want and in pieces, if they’d like, as well as introduces the ability to reroll your NFT traits by making more transactions. ERC404s are inherently fractionalized and designed to work natively with existing DeFi protocols. While innovative, it’s important to note that ERC404 is also experimental.

When we first launched $TRASH, we forked Pandora’s contract and raced to be one of the first, if not the first project to deploy an ERC404 on Base. Pandora’s contract was limited to 5 variations of artwork, images that implied a reveal down the line, so we followed suit with 5 closed-lid NFTs of different rarities. Our next goal was to have a PFP collection with the lids removed, so we came up with the idea to create a new contract where you could stash your $TRASH and mint a Dumpster Diver. This contract is named The Dumpster. It is open source and available to any other ERC404 token that wishes to fork it to enable their holders to redeem their ERC404 token for an ERC721.

In addition to the ability to mint an ERC721 by depositing an ERC404, the Dumpster contract enables holders of Dumpster Divers PFP tokens to burn their ERC721 to redeem the original ERC404 that the ERC721 was minted with (retaining the rarity and token ID). A small cleaning fee (0.00042069 ETH, updatable by governance) is charged, and this mechanism can also be used for regenerating/rerolling or ‘recycling’, Dumpster Diver PFPs to get the desired traits.

We have grown to 185 holders and have generated $44k from trade fees (50% of which is $TRASH and 100% of which is reinvested in providing liquidity for our pools), and 1,654,148 DEGEN (~$40k) from liquidity mining rewards. We were also a finalist in the Backdrop Build V3 Accelerator Program (top 5% of applicants). 

Trash NFTs have built an effective machine: by owning the LPs that facilitate the swaps into $TRASH we capture 1% of the volume and store that in our treasury. We have two liquidity pools: 1) TRASH/ETH and 2) TRASH/ DEGEN, the rapidly growing meme token with utility in the Farcaster network and beyond. This exposes Trash NFTs to volatility, which generates more revenue because arbitrage bots stabilize the price across pools. 

Trash NFTs is also governed by a DAO called Waste Management that was initially allocated 20% of all $TRASH tokens. This DAO collects the cleaning fees associated with trait rerolls as well as the transaction fees and LP rewards from its DeFi activities. Finally, Trash NFTs has entered the meatspace by hosting a trash pickup event during Farcon 2024 with /humankind. 

We are proud of Trash NFTs, as it has maintained and proven to be a sound investment for its holder base while operating successfully. There are definite improvements we continue working toward: 1) expanding growth efforts to the broader 404 ecosystem with partnerships (such as Scattering.io with which we have built a relationship) and promotion, 2) revamping The Dumpster website for a more seamless experience and 3) engaging the community to take leadership in expanding the DAO.

metadata.name: WAVE - N3XTWAVE Collective inaugural drop
metadata.bio:
WAVE was the inaugural drop of N3XTWAVE Collective, which I initiated and organized in September last year. The theme for this drop was discussed collectively, with ‘WAVE’ theme proposed by Francoise Gamma, strongly inspired by our collective's name. ‘WAVE’, representing an impactful force, seemed perfect for a collective drop as it symbolizes our coming together for a simultaneous mint. It also conveys the idea of constant motion, which reflects the ever-evolving Web3 and NFT markets that we actively shape every day.
Given its multiple meanings, we decided to keep the theme open to interpretation for each artist. Each member of the collective created their own ‘WAVE’ - some more literal, others more metaphorical or abstract - each in their personal artistic style and chosen technique. As a result, we have built a collection that is stylistically diverse, ranging from minimalistic and linear to pixelated and glitch aesthetics, making it versatile and appealing to a wide range of tastes. 
Since collaborative contracts were not available on Zora at that time, this drop functions as a collection tied together by a shared art statement that I wrote, which is included in the description of each mint. Here it is:
‿︵‿︵‿︵
WAVE reflects the essence of our collective, signifying our unity through a synchronized mint.
WAVE embodies a powerful force, representing our aspirations as a fresh and influential art group to make a significant impact on the current art scene.
WAVE signifies perpetual motion, mirroring the ever-evolving landscape of Web3 that we actively shape everyday.
Each WAVE mint from N3XTWAVE Collective is a ripple sparking waves of inspiration and creativity, expanding the horizons of artistic expression.
Join us in making waves by minting the WAVE Drop!
■■■ About N3XTWAVE:■■■ N3XTWAVE is an art collective started by artist bleu281 in June 2023. He brought together a small group of visual artists of various generations, styles, backgrounds, and nationalities, yet all based in Europe. United by our exploration of the digital medium, we all experiment with pixels through modern and abandoned digital techniques. 
As of today, N3XTWAVE consists of 17 members from countries including: France, Germany, Poland, Spain, Italy, the UK, Ireland, and the Czech Republic. 
■■■ 
Full details & credits of the WAVE drop: ◆ Initiative, Organizing & Art Statement: V5MT ◆ Promo - Animated Flyers: V5MT ◆ WAVE theme suggestion: Francoise Gamma ◆ N3XTWAVE Animated Logos: Francoise Gamma ◆ PR: V5MT, Ugo Digi ◆ Release Date: September 18th 2023 ◆ Platform: zora.co ◆ Network: ZORA ◆ Artists: Ugo Digi, Bleu281, V5MT, Danctrl, Francoise Gamma, Datura, Lucas Lejeune, mostwrongking, Nicholas Dietrich,  k0ch, Element Lee.
──⬥── 
Notes: 
⬥I'm submitting this project from my personal Farcaster account, not N3XTWAVE, which I also set up, but didn't have time to manage.⬥ Because Zora had no collaborative contracts at the time of the drop, I'm linking to my Mirror article with all the minted pieces embedded, instead of to Zora. + I also included a link to the 'WAVE Drop Organizing' essay I released on Mirror, where I describe the process of organizing this project in detail.⬥I plan to share the potential reward from this submission and distribute it to the artists accordingly.

sunnyAwards.categoryDetails: I really wanted to try out a collective drop on Zora, and I realized I’m part of the N3XTWAVE Collective, so I wrote the concept of the drop, and proposed it to them, and they liked it. In addition to organizing the drop, I created informative documents on how to mint on Zora and explained its mechanics, which were new to most of the artists. I also created animated flyers to promote the event.

metadata.name: WebHash.com
metadata.bio:
Webhash.com is a no-code platform designed to empower users to create tokenised, decentralised, and permanent websites seamlessly. Targeting both ENS (Ethereum Name Service) and traditional DNS domains, users can build and deploy robust websites without any coding knowledge, ensuring their web presence is tamper-proof and enduring. These websites are deployed on IPFS (InterPlanetary File System) and tokenised on Base, providing enhanced security, immutability, and ownership verification, setting a new standard in website development and management.

Tokenisation: Each website created on Webhash.com is tokenised on the Base blockchain. This means that every website is represented by a unique token, ensuring clear ownership and provenance. Tokenisation allows for easy transfer and trading of website ownership, creating a seamless and secure way to manage web properties.

Decentralisation: By deploying websites on IPFS, Webhash.com leverages a distributed network of nodes to store and serve content. This decentralised approach eliminates single points of failure, making websites more resilient to censorship and server outages. It ensures that the content remains accessible as long as the network exists, without relying on any central authority.

Permanence: The combination of IPFS and Filecoin ensures that websites are permanent and immutable. Once content is added to IPFS, it is distributed across multiple nodes, making it tamper-proof. Our smart contract on base provides an immutable ledger of ownership and changes, guaranteeing that once a website is created and tokenised, its history and content cannot be altered or erased.

Permanence: The combination of IPFS and Filecoin ensures that websites are permanent and immutable. Once content is added to IPFS, it is distributed across multiple nodes, making it tamper-proof. Our smart contract on base provides an immutable ledger of ownership and changes, guaranteeing that once a website is created and tokenised, its history and content cannot be altered or erased.

📈 Our Growth in Numbers:
User Engagement: We've welcomed over 3,045 users, a testament to the growing interest and trust in decentralised web solutions.
Website Creations: Our platform has enabled the creation of 4,527 decentralised websites, showcasing the diverse applications and creativity of our community.
Storage Expansion: We're now utilising 95 GB on IPFS, highlighting our commitment to robust and decentralised storage solutions.

Partnerships: 

In our continuous effort to enhance and expand the capabilities of Webhash within the ENS ecosystem, we've taken significant strides in integrating products build within the ENS ecosystem that empower our users and their decentralised creations. 

🌐 Eth.limo: Eth.limo has become an integral part of the Webhash ecosystem, providing a seamless way to access decentralised websites with a ".limo" extension. This integration means every decentralised website created on Webhash is automatically generated with a .limo extension, ensuring a uniform and recognizable domain system for users and visitors alike. Furthermore, all content created on Webhash is pinned on Eth.limo's IPFS node, which not only enhances the reliability and speed of content delivery but also strengthens the decentralised nature of our hosting solutions.

Our collaboration with Eth.limo is further enhanced through the integration of Eth.limo's API, including their Domain over HTTPS (DoH) API, into the Webhash ENS website resolver (browser extension). This advanced integration leverages @ethlimo.eth’s DoH API to efficiently fetch the corresponding IPFS hash or Arweave link associated with a .eth domain. This capability streamlines the process of linking ENS domains to their corresponding decentralised content, ensuring a seamless and efficient resolution system for decentralised web access. 

🌍 Namespace: With the integration of Namespace, users can mint subdomains directly on Webhash, offering a layer of personalization and organisation to their decentralised web presence. These subdomains provide a scalable way for users to categorise, manage, and deploy multiple decentralised websites under a unified domain structure, further enriching the Webhash ecosystem.

🔄 Ethereum Follow Protocol (EFP): In an exciting development, we're implementing a new feature that allows users to showcase their Ethereum Follow Protocol (EFP) numbers directly on their decentralised websites. This block, when added to a site on Webhash, not only highlights the user's engagement within the Ethereum community but also fosters a sense of connectivity and social proof among decentralised web participants. The Ethereum Follow Protocol integration signifies our commitment to leveraging blockchain technology not just for hosting but also for community building and engagement.

🔨 Community Engagement through Buildathons: Our mission to ignite active participation within the ENS community has led to the creation of decentralised websites for ENS domains through Webhash. Our Buildathons, including collaborations like frENS, are key to empowering individuals to develop innovative decentralised digital identities.

Buildathon 1: We gave $1000 to five winners who build decentralised websites
Buildathon 2: Done in collaboration with frENS. We gave $1000 to five winners who build decentralised websites.
Buildathon 3: Still in progress we a giving $1200 to five winners


Key features of Webhash: 

No-Code Interface: We've created a no-code, user-friendly interface that makes building decentralised websites accessible to everyone, regardless of technical expertise.
Versatile Content Creation & Integration: Our platform at Webhash enriches the ENS domain experience by enabling users to create a broad spectrum of content types with seamless integrations. We have designed a user-friendly interface that allows for the addition of various standard elements such as avatars with diverse styles, engaging headings, informative paragraphs, and external links, all of which enhance the user's webpage. The integration capabilities of our platform include a suite of options that cater to different media types and functionalities:

Social Media Integration: Users can showcase their social presence with icons linked to their profiles on platforms like Twitter, Instagram, Facebook, and more, fostering engagement directly from their ENS dwebsite.

Multimedia Content: Embedding capabilities for platforms like YouTube, Vimeo, Twitch, Spotify, and SoundCloud allow users to share a wide range of audiovisual content, from music tracks and podcasts to videos and livestreams.

Web3 activity blocks: Integrated key web3 projects like Farcaster and POAP so that users can showcase their web3 activity. 

Interactive Features: Inclusion of interactive elements such as image sliders, RSS feeds, countdown widgets, and forms elevates the user experience by engaging visitors with dynamic content.
Content Distribution: Our platform supports file sharing directly from the page, whether it’s audio files, PDF documents, or any downloadable content, making it a versatile tool for content distribution.
Communication and Sharing: Integration of communication tools like Discord servers and call-to-action prompts encourages community building and interaction. Additionally, our VCard feature enables users to share contact information in a professional manner.

Monetization: We've integrated payment solutions like PayPal, enabling users to collect payments for products, services, or donations directly through their ENS decentralised website.

Customization: Advanced customization with custom HTML/CSS/JS and Markdown formatting allows for unique content creation. 

Credibility and Engagement: By adding customer reviews and FAQs, users can build credibility and provide valuable information to their audience.

The combination of these features on the Webhash platform not only empowers users to create comprehensive 'link-in-bio' pages but also extends to more complex decentralised website formats such as blogs, portfolios, and business landing pages. Each feature is designed to be intuitive and easy to use, ensuring that even those with no coding skills can build a professional and aesthetically pleasing online presence on the decentralised web.

Seamless ENS and DNS Domain Connections: We've streamlined the process of connecting ENS and traditional DNS domains to decentralised websites, making it hassle-free and efficient.
Collaboration with ETH.limo: We've partnered with ETH.limo to ensure optimal speed and availability for the decentralised websites hosted on our platform.

Monetization Through NFTs: We've innovated in monetization by allowing users to mint their website designs as NFTs, creating new economic opportunities within the ENS ecosystem.
Arweave Integration: Our integration with Arweave enables a persistent web presence, ensuring durability and longevity of the content.

Setting Resolvers for Domains: We've simplified the process of setting resolvers for ENS domains, addressing a common challenge faced by users.

Subdomain and Wrapped Domain Support: We've Introduced support for both subdomains and wrapped domains. This feature lets users build and manage a network of decentralised websites under one ENS domain. Whether it’s for different projects, services, or varied content types, our users can now efficiently organise their online presence.

metadata.name: Xottle : Tokenized Bottle Waste
metadata.bio:
Xottle: Tokenized Bottle Waste Platform addresses the pressing issue of plastic waste by creating a system that encourages and rewards recycling.
Here's how Xottle makes a difference:

1. Incentivizing Recycling
People often lack motivation to recycle due to the absence of immediate rewards. Xottle solves this by rewarding users with $XOTL tokens for every bottle they recycle. These tokens can be used to purchase merchandise or access exclusive benefits, turning recycling into a rewarding activity.

2. Transparency and Trust
Traditional recycling programs can be opaque, leading to mistrust. Xottle leverages blockchain technology to ensure transparency, recording every recycled bottle and transaction on the blockchain. This provides users with verifiable proof that their recycling efforts are contributing positively to the environment.

3. Gamifying the Experience
Recycling is often seen as mundane, which can lead to disengagement. Xottle makes recycling engaging through challenges and leaderboards, where users can earn badges and compete to see who can recycle the most. This gamification keeps users motivated and involved.

4. Simplifying the Process
The complexity of recycling can deter participation. Xottle simplifies this by allowing users to scan a QR code on each bottle, instantly registering their recycling and earning rewards. This makes recycling as easy as scanning a code, lowering the barrier to participation.

Summary
Xottle is a platform that combines financial incentives, gamification, and blockchain transparency to make recycling easier, more engaging, and rewarding. By transforming the way people perceive and participate in recycling, Xottle contributes to reducing plastic waste and promoting a more sustainable future. This solution is not just for individuals, but also for companies and organizations looking to enhance their sustainability initiatives.

metadata.name: ZNS Connect
metadata.bio:
ZNS Connect is a decentralized naming system designed to simplify Web3 by offering user-friendly and memorable domain names. Our platform enhances digital identities and smooth transactions across multiple blockchains.

ZNS Connect is a decentralized naming system designed to revolutionize the Web3 experience by replacing complex addresses with user-friendly and memorable domain names. ZNS Connect aims to streamline interactions within the blockchain ecosystem, providing a seamless experience for users.

Our mission is to simplify Web3 for users, offering easy-to-remember digital identities that enhance their online presence and facilitate smooth transactions across various blockchains. The ZNS Connect app provides a cohesive platform where users can manage their digital identities, ensuring efficient Web3 interactions.

Enjoy personalized Web3 pages, enhanced security with alphanumeric wallet addresses, and seamless access to DEXs, wallets, and apps using ZNS domain names. By leveraging the power of decentralized technologies, ZNS Connect empowers users to engage with the Web3 world confidently and conveniently, making blockchain technology more accessible and user-friendly. Join us in transforming the digital landscape with ZNS Connect, your gateway to a simplified and integrated Web3 experience.
